<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ Mettanna</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(To the end)</font></i>

21
00:03:37,333 --> 00:03:39,200
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ Nárendur</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Servant of fire)</font></i>

22
00:03:39,333 --> 00:03:43,200
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ An mauya mahtie</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(For you must fight)</font></i>

23
00:03:43,333 --> 00:03:48,200
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ Mettana</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(To the end)</font></i>

24
00:03:50,507 --> 00:03:52,295
Gandalf!

25
00:03:53,376 --> 00:03:55,482
What is it, Mr. Frodo?

26
00:03:57,547 --> 00:03:59,238
Nothing.

27
00:04:06,523 --> 00:04:08,497
Just a dream.

28
00:04:21,738 --> 00:04:23,014
Can you see the bottom?

29
00:04:24,309 --> 00:04:27,275
No! Don't look down, Sam!
Just keep going!

30
00:04:38,257 --> 00:04:40,296
Catch it! Grab it, Mr. Frodo!

31
00:04:43,461 --> 00:04:45,347
Mr. Frodo!

32
00:04:48,099 --> 00:04:49,659
I think I've found the bottom.

33
00:04:55,240 --> 00:04:58,109
Bogs and rope,
and goodness knows what.

34
00:04:58,376 --> 00:05:01,441
It's not natural. None of it.

35
00:05:04,649 --> 00:05:06,624
- What's in this?
- Nothing.

36
00:05:08,153 --> 00:05:09,200
Just a bit of seasoning.

37
00:05:09,721 --> 00:05:12,438
I thought maybe if we was having
a roast chicken one night or something.

38
00:05:13,192 --> 00:05:15,264
Roast chicken?!

39
00:05:16,027 --> 00:05:17,205
You never know.

40
00:05:17,662 --> 00:05:20,476
Sam. My dear Sam.

41
00:05:22,369 --> 00:05:26,143
It's very special, that.
It's the best salt in all the Shire.

42
00:05:27,539 --> 00:05:29,448
It is special.

43
00:05:33,445 --> 00:05:35,267
It's a little bit of home.

44
00:05:38,617 --> 00:05:41,039
We can't leave this here for someone
to follow us down.

45
00:05:41,521 --> 00:05:44,968
Who's gonna follow us down here,
Mr. Frodo?

46
00:05:45,959 --> 00:05:49,503
It's a shame, really.
Lady Galadriel gave me that.

47
00:05:50,430 --> 00:05:52,284
Real Elvish rope.

48
00:05:53,265 --> 00:05:55,503
Well, there's nothing for it.
It's one of my knots.

49
00:05:55,770 --> 00:05:57,656
Won't come free in a hurry.

50
00:06:06,612 --> 00:06:08,816
Real Elvish rope.

51
00:06:23,029 --> 00:06:27,252
Mordor. The one place in Middle-earth
we don't want to see any closer.

52
00:06:27,568 --> 00:06:29,640
And it's the one place
we're trying to get to.

53
00:06:30,538 --> 00:06:32,261
It's just where we can't get.

54
00:06:33,741 --> 00:06:36,555
Let's face it, Mr. Frodo, we're lost.

55
00:06:39,146 --> 00:06:41,829
I don't think Gandalf meant for us to
come this way.

56
00:06:43,485 --> 00:06:46,582
He didn't mean for a lot of things
to happen, Sam...

57
00:06:47,588 --> 00:06:49,083
...but they did.

58
00:07:02,270 --> 00:07:03,131
Mr. Frodo?

59
00:07:07,141 --> 00:07:08,418
It's the Ring, isn't it?

60
00:07:09,578 --> 00:07:11,998
It's getting heavier.

61
00:07:24,659 --> 00:07:27,310
- What food have we got left?
- Let me see.

62
00:07:28,197 --> 00:07:30,171
Oh, yes. Lovely.

63
00:07:30,399 --> 00:07:33,083
Lembas bread. And look!

64
00:07:35,570 --> 00:07:37,872
More lembas bread.

65
00:07:48,618 --> 00:07:50,505
I don't usually hold with foreign food...

66
00:07:50,753 --> 00:07:53,600
...but this Elvish stuff, it's not bad.

67
00:07:54,624 --> 00:07:58,039
Nothing ever dampens your spirits,
does it, Sam?

68
00:08:04,033 --> 00:08:06,172
Those rain clouds might.

69
00:08:40,538 --> 00:08:43,220
This looks strangely familiar.

70
00:08:43,974 --> 00:08:46,308
It's because we've been here before.

71
00:08:46,577 --> 00:08:49,099
We're going in circles.

72
00:08:49,982 --> 00:08:51,639
What is that horrid stink?

73
00:08:52,015 --> 00:08:54,088
I warrant there's a nasty bog nearby.

74
00:08:54,319 --> 00:08:56,206
- Can you smell it?
- Yes.

75
00:08:58,322 --> 00:09:00,395
I can smell it.

76
00:09:03,662 --> 00:09:06,083
We're not alone.

77
00:09:19,912 --> 00:09:23,839
The thieves. The thieves.

78
00:09:24,149 --> 00:09:27,945
The filthy little thieves.

79
00:09:28,687 --> 00:09:30,890
Where is it?

80
00:09:31,155 --> 00:09:33,610
Where is it?

81
00:09:34,460 --> 00:09:37,526
They stole it from us.

82
00:09:37,964 --> 00:09:41,957
My precious.

83
00:09:43,035 --> 00:09:46,100
Curse them, we hates them!

84
00:09:46,405 --> 00:09:50,300
It's ours, it is, and we wants it!

85
00:10:45,566 --> 00:10:47,322
This is Sting.

86
00:10:47,535 --> 00:10:49,095
You've seen it before...

87
00:10:49,303 --> 00:10:51,637
...haven't you, Gollum?

88
00:10:55,777 --> 00:10:59,191
Release him or I'll cut your throat.

89
00:11:15,364 --> 00:11:17,119
It burns!

90
00:11:17,332 --> 00:11:19,470
It burns us!

91
00:11:21,135 --> 00:11:22,477
It freezes!

92
00:11:24,373 --> 00:11:26,478
Nasty Elves twisted it.

93
00:11:26,743 --> 00:11:29,328
- Take it off us!
- Quiet, you!

94
00:11:32,981 --> 00:11:37,006
It's hopeless. Every Orc in Mordor's
going to hear this racket.

95
00:11:37,351 --> 00:11:39,872
- Let's just tie him up and leave him.
- No!

96
00:11:40,222 --> 00:11:43,518
That would kill us! Kill us!

97
00:11:43,793 --> 00:11:46,410
It's no more than you deserve!

98
00:11:48,264 --> 00:11:50,238
Maybe he does deserve to die.

99
00:11:52,635 --> 00:11:56,049
But now that I see him, I do pity him.

100
00:11:59,575 --> 00:12:04,211
We be nice to them
if they be nice to us.

101
00:12:04,614 --> 00:12:07,297
Take it off us.

102
00:12:10,520 --> 00:12:14,317
We swears to do what you wants.

103
00:12:14,625 --> 00:12:16,479
We swears.

104
00:12:16,994 --> 00:12:19,262
There's no promise you can make
that I can trust.

105
00:12:22,065 --> 00:12:23,625
We swears...

106
00:12:24,068 --> 00:12:28,508
...to serve the master
of the precious.

107
00:12:30,407 --> 00:12:32,578
We will swear on...

108
00:12:32,977 --> 00:12:34,699
...on the precious.

109
00:12:35,111 --> 00:12:37,184
Gollum. Gollum.

110
00:12:37,414 --> 00:12:41,342
The Ring is treacherous.
It will hold you to your word.

111
00:12:42,386 --> 00:12:43,596
Yes...

112
00:12:44,322 --> 00:12:46,624
...on the precious.

113
00:12:49,193 --> 00:12:51,463
On the precious.

114
00:12:52,730 --> 00:12:54,224
I don't believe you!

115
00:12:56,301 --> 00:12:59,562
- Get down! I said, down!
- Sam!

116
00:13:00,071 --> 00:13:01,566
He's trying to trick us.

117
00:13:01,774 --> 00:13:04,806
If we let him go, he'll throttle us
in our sleep.

118
00:13:16,288 --> 00:13:20,565
- You know the way to Mordor?
- Yes.

119
00:13:23,695 --> 00:13:25,418
You've been there before?

120
00:13:26,498 --> 00:13:28,090
Yes.

121
00:13:39,078 --> 00:13:41,466
You will lead us to the Black Gate.

122
00:13:50,256 --> 00:13:53,998
To the Gate, to the Gate!
To the Gate, the master says. Yes!

123
00:13:54,293 --> 00:13:58,930
No! We won't go back.
Not there. Not to him.

124
00:13:59,265 --> 00:14:03,291
They can't make us. Gollum! Gollum!

125
00:14:03,604 --> 00:14:06,985
But we swore to serve the master
of the precious.

126
00:14:07,307 --> 00:14:13,023
No. Ashes and dust and thirst there is,
and pits, pits, pits.

127
00:14:13,413 --> 00:14:16,194
And Orcses, thousands of Orcses.

128
00:14:16,448 --> 00:14:21,369
And always the Great Eye watching,
watching.

129
00:14:24,559 --> 00:14:28,235
Hey! Come back now! Come back!

130
00:14:30,730 --> 00:14:32,999
There! What did I tell you?

131
00:14:33,233 --> 00:14:35,338
He's run off, the old villain.

132
00:14:35,570 --> 00:14:38,057
So much for his promises.

133
00:14:38,339 --> 00:14:39,932
This way, Hobbits.

134
00:14:40,207 --> 00:14:42,149
Follow me!

135
00:14:56,123 --> 00:14:57,399
Merry!

136
00:14:58,426 --> 00:14:59,920
Merry!

137
00:15:05,433 --> 00:15:09,078
You're late.
Our master grows impatient.

138
00:15:09,370 --> 00:15:11,159
He wants the Shire-rats now.

139
00:15:12,107 --> 00:15:16,416
I don't take orders from Orc-maggots.

140
00:15:17,645 --> 00:15:20,579
Saruman will have his prize.

141
00:15:21,016 --> 00:15:24,049
We will deliver them.

142
00:15:30,360 --> 00:15:31,603
Merry!

143
00:15:32,461 --> 00:15:34,183
Merry? Wake up.

144
00:15:37,667 --> 00:15:39,455
My friend is sick.

145
00:15:40,069 --> 00:15:42,524
He needs water. Please!

146
00:15:43,405 --> 00:15:47,202
Sick, is he?
Give him some medicine, boys!

147
00:15:50,579 --> 00:15:52,204
Stop it!

148
00:15:54,450 --> 00:15:57,035
Can't take his draught!

149
00:15:59,722 --> 00:16:02,242
- Leave him alone!
- Why?

150
00:16:02,926 --> 00:16:05,195
You want some?

151
00:16:06,061 --> 00:16:09,226
Then keep your mouth shut.

152
00:16:12,702 --> 00:16:14,644
Merry.

153
00:16:15,638 --> 00:16:17,165
Hello, Pip.

154
00:16:19,075 --> 00:16:21,344
- You're hurt.
- I'm fine.

155
00:16:21,577 --> 00:16:24,065
- It was just an act.
- An act?

156
00:16:24,747 --> 00:16:27,497
See? I fooled you too.

157
00:16:30,387 --> 00:16:32,077
Don't worry about me, Pippin.

158
00:16:34,425 --> 00:16:36,334
What is it? What do you smell?

159
00:16:37,393 --> 00:16:38,572
Man-flesh.

160
00:16:40,764 --> 00:16:43,131
They've picked up our trail.

161
00:16:44,336 --> 00:16:45,383
Aragorn.

162
00:16:47,205 --> 00:16:48,960
Let's move!

163
00:17:12,498 --> 00:17:14,985
Their pace has quickened.

164
00:17:16,134 --> 00:17:18,021
They must have caught our scent.

165
00:17:18,236 --> 00:17:19,958
Hurry!

166
00:17:23,575 --> 00:17:25,298
Come on, Gimli!

167
00:17:29,214 --> 00:17:31,385
Three days and nights pursuit.

168
00:17:31,617 --> 00:17:34,463
No food. No rest.

169
00:17:34,753 --> 00:17:38,550
And no sign of our quarry,
but what bare rock can tell.

170
00:18:10,256 --> 00:18:13,255
Not idly do the leaves of Lórien fall.

171
00:18:14,694 --> 00:18:17,061
They may yet be alive.

172
00:18:18,031 --> 00:18:20,452
Less than a day ahead of us. Come.

173
00:18:23,236 --> 00:18:25,538
Come, Gimli! We're gaining on them!

174
00:18:25,972 --> 00:18:30,030
I'm wasted on cross-country.
We Dwarves are natural sprinters.

175
00:18:30,644 --> 00:18:33,873
Very dangerous over short distances.

176
00:18:45,659 --> 00:18:47,350
Rohan.

177
00:18:47,594 --> 00:18:50,311
Home of the Horse-lords.

178
00:18:51,599 --> 00:18:54,119
There's something strange at work here.

179
00:18:54,368 --> 00:18:57,215
Some evil gives speed
to these creatures.

180
00:18:57,504 --> 00:19:00,351
Sets its will against us.

181
00:19:05,614 --> 00:19:08,396
Legolas! What do your Elf-eyes see?

182
00:19:08,649 --> 00:19:11,168
The Uruks turn northeast.

183
00:19:12,153 --> 00:19:14,192
They are taking the Hobbits to Isengard.

184
00:19:15,189 --> 00:19:16,333
Saruman.

185
00:19:24,932 --> 00:19:27,965
The world is changing.

186
00:19:28,237 --> 00:19:33,506
Who now has the strength to stand
against the armies of Isengard...

187
00:19:34,476 --> 00:19:37,159
...and Mordor?

188
00:19:39,014 --> 00:19:44,316
<i>To stand against the might of Sauron
and Saruman...</i>

189
00:19:44,686 --> 00:19:48,231
...and the union of the two towers?

190
00:19:54,963 --> 00:19:57,833
Together, my Lord Sauron...

191
00:19:58,101 --> 00:20:01,396
...we shall rule this Middle-earth.

192
00:20:17,620 --> 00:20:21,810
The Old World will burn
in the fires of industry.

193
00:20:22,458 --> 00:20:25,556
The forests will fall.

194
00:20:27,630 --> 00:20:30,380
A new order will rise.

195
00:20:31,569 --> 00:20:36,303
We will drive the machine of war
with the sword and the spear...

196
00:20:36,639 --> 00:20:40,436
...and the iron fists of the Orc.

197
00:20:53,189 --> 00:20:56,256
I want them armed and ready to march
within two weeks!

198
00:20:56,527 --> 00:20:58,152
But, my lord, there are too many!

199
00:20:58,361 --> 00:21:01,263
They cannot all be armed in time,
we don't have the means.

200
00:21:01,532 --> 00:21:04,467
Build a dam, block the stream,
work the furnaces night and day.

201
00:21:05,303 --> 00:21:07,506
We don't have enough fuel
to feed the fires.

202
00:21:09,075 --> 00:21:13,133
The Forest of Fangorn
lies on our doorstep.

203
00:21:14,645 --> 00:21:17,011
- Burn it.
- Yes.

204
00:21:17,717 --> 00:21:20,017
We will fight for you.

205
00:21:20,252 --> 00:21:22,161
Swear it.

206
00:21:32,665 --> 00:21:37,301
We will die for Saruman.

207
00:21:38,570 --> 00:21:40,480
The Horse-Men took your lands.

208
00:21:40,706 --> 00:21:45,145
They drove your people into the hills
to scratch a living off rocks.

209
00:21:45,477 --> 00:21:46,939
Murderers!

210
00:21:47,747 --> 00:21:49,950
Take back the lands they stole from you.

211
00:21:50,181 --> 00:21:51,937
Burn every village!

212
00:21:55,186 --> 00:22:00,075
We have only to remove those
who oppose us.

213
00:22:00,693 --> 00:22:03,180
It will begin in Rohan.

214
00:22:04,096 --> 00:22:07,391
Too long have these peasants
stood against you.

215
00:22:07,667 --> 00:22:09,423
But no more.

216
00:22:09,634 --> 00:22:11,936
Éothain! Éothain!

217
00:22:13,100 --> 00:22:24,700
<i><font color="#800080">♫ And on thaere hwile</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(And in that moment)</font></i>

218
00:22:14,174 --> 00:22:16,629
You take your sister.
You'll go faster with just two.

219
00:22:17,210 --> 00:22:19,664
Papa says Éothain must not ride Garulf.

220
00:22:20,079 --> 00:22:21,573
He is too big for him.

221
00:22:21,781 --> 00:22:24,650
Listen to me. You must ride to Edoras
and raise the alarm.

222
00:22:25,070 --> 00:22:44,700
<i><font color="#800080">♫ Héo[dréag] thá losinga</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(She felt the loss)</font></i>

223
00:22:25,084 --> 00:22:27,418
- Do you understand me?
- Yes, Mama.

224
00:22:27,753 --> 00:22:30,569
I don't want to leave.
I don't want to go, Mama.

225
00:22:30,992 --> 00:22:34,438
Freda, I will find you there.

226
00:22:39,533 --> 00:22:41,224
Quickly!

227
00:22:45,100 --> 00:23:02,700
<i><font color="#800080">♫ Earla thinga the héo forléas</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Of everything that had been missed)</font></i>

228
00:22:47,642 --> 00:22:49,201
Go, child.

229
00:23:02,156 --> 00:23:04,011
Rohan, my lord...

230
00:23:04,460 --> 00:23:07,109
...is ready to fall.

231
00:23:18,473 --> 00:23:20,000
Théodred.

232
00:23:20,241 --> 00:23:21,702
Find the king's son!

233
00:23:38,293 --> 00:23:44,075
- Mordor will pay for this.
- These Orcs are not from Mordor.

234
00:23:45,266 --> 00:23:48,017
My Lord Éomer, over here!

235
00:23:56,811 --> 00:23:58,568
He's alive.

236
00:24:29,478 --> 00:24:31,453
Théodred.

237
00:24:45,028 --> 00:24:47,930
Your son is badly wounded, my lord.

238
00:24:48,398 --> 00:24:50,701
He was ambushed by Orcs.

239
00:24:52,436 --> 00:24:55,981
If we don't defend our country,
Saruman will take it by force.

240
00:24:56,440 --> 00:24:58,894
That is a lie.

241
00:25:01,212 --> 00:25:05,817
Saruman the White has ever been
our friend and ally.

242
00:25:07,551 --> 00:25:09,492
Grima.

243
00:25:11,089 --> 00:25:12,976
Grima.

244
00:25:15,494 --> 00:25:17,020
Grima.

245
00:25:17,761 --> 00:25:20,827
Orcs are roaming freely
across our lands.

246
00:25:21,298 --> 00:25:24,812
Unchecked. Unchallenged.
Killing at will.

247
00:25:25,537 --> 00:25:28,351
Orcs bearing the White Hand of Saruman.

248
00:25:36,347 --> 00:25:41,911
Why do you lay these troubles
on an already troubled mind?

249
00:25:42,287 --> 00:25:44,588
Can you not see?

250
00:25:44,990 --> 00:25:49,845
Your uncle is wearied
by your malcontent...

251
00:25:50,195 --> 00:25:52,528
...your warmongering.

252
00:25:54,800 --> 00:25:56,708
Warmongering?

253
00:25:57,102 --> 00:25:59,142
How long is it since
Saruman bought you?

254
00:26:00,105 --> 00:26:02,308
What was the promised price, Grima?

255
00:26:02,607 --> 00:26:06,120
When all the Men are dead,
you will take your share of the treasure?

256
00:26:18,659 --> 00:26:21,243
Too long have you watched my sister.

257
00:26:21,526 --> 00:26:23,436
Too long have you haunted her steps.

258
00:26:31,571 --> 00:26:35,826
You see much, Éomer, son of Éomund.

259
00:26:36,142 --> 00:26:37,223
Too much.

260
00:26:39,579 --> 00:26:44,216
You are banished forthwith
from the kingdom of Rohan...

261
00:26:44,551 --> 00:26:49,187
...and all its domains
under pain of death.

262
00:26:49,756 --> 00:26:52,123
You have no authority here.

263
00:26:52,359 --> 00:26:54,660
Your orders mean nothing.

264
00:26:55,361 --> 00:26:59,071
This order does not come from me.

265
00:26:59,366 --> 00:27:01,407
It comes from the king.

266
00:27:02,170 --> 00:27:04,558
He signed it this morning.

267
00:27:25,749 --> 00:27:35,200
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ [Ró]mello vanwa, [Va]limar!</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Lost to those of the East is Valimar!)</font></i>

268
00:27:35,749 --> 00:27:44,200
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ Namarie! Nai [elye] hiru[va]!</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Farewell! Maybe even thou shalt find it!)</font></i>

269
00:27:36,304 --> 00:27:38,954
Keep breathing. That's the key.

270
00:27:39,272 --> 00:27:40,931
Breathe.

271
00:27:44,749 --> 00:27:55,200
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ [Ró]mello vanwa, [Va]limar!</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Lost to those of the East is Valimar!)</font></i>

272
00:27:45,114 --> 00:27:48,822
They've run as if the very whips
of their masters were behind them.

273
00:27:55,749 --> 00:28:03,200
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ Nai elyë [hiruva!]</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Maybe even thou shalt find it!)</font></i>

274
00:28:05,067 --> 00:28:07,009
We're not going no further...

275
00:28:07,236 --> 00:28:09,146
...until we've had a breather.

276
00:28:09,706 --> 00:28:11,592
Get a fire going!

277
00:28:15,745 --> 00:28:17,305
Merry!

278
00:28:17,680 --> 00:28:19,055
Merry!

279
00:28:20,717 --> 00:28:25,833
I think we might have made a mistake
leaving the Shire, Pippin.

280
00:28:35,432 --> 00:28:37,504
What's making that noise?

281
00:28:39,269 --> 00:28:40,578
It's the trees.

282
00:28:41,437 --> 00:28:42,420
What?

283
00:28:42,772 --> 00:28:46,448
You remember the Old Forest,
on the borders of Buckland?

284
00:28:46,776 --> 00:28:51,150
Folk used to say there was something in
the water that made the trees grow tall...

285
00:28:51,514 --> 00:28:53,041
...and come alive.

286
00:28:53,317 --> 00:28:54,974
Alive?

287
00:28:55,786 --> 00:28:57,444
Trees that could whisper...

288
00:28:58,555 --> 00:29:00,976
...talk to each other...

289
00:29:01,224 --> 00:29:02,981
...even move.

290
00:29:04,562 --> 00:29:06,831
I'm starving.

291
00:29:07,065 --> 00:29:10,959
We ain't had nothing but maggoty bread
for three stinking days.

292
00:29:11,435 --> 00:29:12,612
Yeah!

293
00:29:13,003 --> 00:29:16,102
Why can't we have some meat?!

294
00:29:18,542 --> 00:29:20,614
What about them?

295
00:29:21,012 --> 00:29:22,866
They're fresh.

296
00:29:23,481 --> 00:29:27,125
They are not for eating.

297
00:29:33,290 --> 00:29:35,177
What about their legs?

298
00:29:35,394 --> 00:29:37,597
They don't need those.

299
00:29:39,230 --> 00:29:42,230
- They look tasty.
- Get back, scum!

300
00:29:44,235 --> 00:29:48,937
The prisoners go to Saruman.
Alive and unspoiled.

301
00:29:49,440 --> 00:29:51,329
Alive?

302
00:29:54,379 --> 00:29:58,437
Why alive?
Do they give good sport?

303
00:30:01,120 --> 00:30:04,283
They have something.
An Elvish weapon.

304
00:30:04,557 --> 00:30:07,459
The master wants it for the war.

305
00:30:10,496 --> 00:30:12,318
They think we have the Ring.

306
00:30:12,531 --> 00:30:14,953
As soon as they find out we don't,
we're dead.

307
00:30:16,768 --> 00:30:18,678
Just a mouthful...

308
00:30:19,071 --> 00:30:20,183
...a bit of the flank.

309
00:30:27,079 --> 00:30:30,395
Looks like meat's back on the menu,
boys.

310
00:30:37,223 --> 00:30:38,402
Pippin.

311
00:30:38,592 --> 00:30:40,282
Let's go.

312
00:30:48,701 --> 00:30:50,228
Go on.

313
00:30:50,469 --> 00:30:51,963
Call for help.

314
00:30:53,341 --> 00:30:54,388
Squeal.

315
00:30:54,608 --> 00:30:57,608
No one's going to save you now.

316
00:31:07,053 --> 00:31:08,330
Pippin!

317
00:31:32,648 --> 00:31:35,102
A red sun rises.

318
00:31:35,649 --> 00:31:38,464
Blood has been spilled this night.

319
00:32:09,717 --> 00:32:11,539
Riders of Rohan...

320
00:32:12,155 --> 00:32:14,423
...what news from the Mark?

321
00:32:42,318 --> 00:32:46,475
What business does an Elf, a Man
and a Dwarf have in the Riddermark?

322
00:32:47,490 --> 00:32:48,635
Speak quickly!

323
00:32:49,160 --> 00:32:53,534
Give me your name, horse-master,
and I shall give you mine.

324
00:33:02,806 --> 00:33:05,294
I would cut off your head, Dwarf...

325
00:33:05,775 --> 00:33:08,164
...if it stood but a little higher
from the ground.

326
00:33:09,279 --> 00:33:11,253
You would die before your stroke fell.

327
00:33:20,124 --> 00:33:21,946
I am Aragorn, son of Arathorn.

328
00:33:22,326 --> 00:33:26,318
This is Gimli, son of Glóin,
and Legolas of the Woodland Realm.

329
00:33:26,629 --> 00:33:29,858
We are friends of Rohan
and of Théoden, your king.

330
00:33:31,602 --> 00:33:35,246
Théoden no longer recognizes
friend from foe.

331
00:33:35,606 --> 00:33:37,647
Not even his own kin.

332
00:33:42,347 --> 00:33:44,234
Saruman has poisoned the mind
of the king...

333
00:33:44,483 --> 00:33:46,337
...and claimed lordship over these lands.

334
00:33:48,387 --> 00:33:51,257
My company are those loyal to Rohan.

335
00:33:51,556 --> 00:33:53,279
And for that, we are banished.

336
00:33:55,394 --> 00:33:58,525
The White Wizard is cunning.

337
00:33:59,397 --> 00:34:01,634
He walks here and there, they say...

338
00:34:02,034 --> 00:34:03,922
...as an old man hooded and cloaked.

339
00:34:05,737 --> 00:34:09,414
And everywhere, his spies
slip past our nets.

340
00:34:09,708 --> 00:34:11,977
We are no spies.

341
00:34:12,211 --> 00:34:15,025
We track a party of Uruk-hai
westward across the plain.

342
00:34:15,413 --> 00:34:17,585
They have taken two of our friends
captive.

343
00:34:18,518 --> 00:34:20,973
The Uruks are destroyed.
We slaughtered them during the night.

344
00:34:21,221 --> 00:34:24,219
But there were two Hobbits.
Did you see two Hobbits with them?

345
00:34:24,489 --> 00:34:27,359
They would be small.
Only children to your eyes.

346
00:34:30,763 --> 00:34:32,672
We left none alive.

347
00:34:33,465 --> 00:34:36,281
We piled the carcasses and burned them.

348
00:34:41,809 --> 00:34:43,117
Dead?

349
00:34:46,179 --> 00:34:47,705
I am sorry.

350
00:34:53,420 --> 00:34:55,591
Hasufel! Arod!

351
00:34:57,523 --> 00:35:02,029
May these horses bear you to better
fortune than their former masters.

352
00:35:03,396 --> 00:35:04,989
Farewell.

353
00:35:10,204 --> 00:35:12,342
Look for your friends.

354
00:35:12,973 --> 00:35:15,078
But do not trust to hope.

355
00:35:16,743 --> 00:35:19,263
It has forsaken these lands.

356
00:35:19,580 --> 00:35:21,468
We ride north!

357
00:36:12,234 --> 00:36:14,022
It's one of their wee belts.

358
00:36:15,000 --> 00:36:19,000
<font color="#008000">Hiro hyn hîdh ab ’wanath.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(Let they find peace in the afterlife.)</font>

359
00:36:27,783 --> 00:36:29,692
We failed them.

360
00:36:44,034 --> 00:36:46,074
A Hobbit lay here.

361
00:36:48,071 --> 00:36:49,532
And the other.

362
00:37:00,451 --> 00:37:02,043
They crawled.

363
00:37:06,189 --> 00:37:08,163
Their hands were bound.

364
00:37:20,404 --> 00:37:22,192
Their bonds were cut.

365
00:37:37,654 --> 00:37:39,662
They ran over here.

366
00:37:43,495 --> 00:37:44,574
They were followed.

367
00:37:47,999 --> 00:37:49,526
The belt!

368
00:37:53,538 --> 00:37:54,585
Run!

369
00:37:58,409 --> 00:37:59,620
Tracks lead away from the battle...

370
00:38:04,516 --> 00:38:06,490
...into Fangorn Forest.

371
00:38:07,519 --> 00:38:08,980
Fangorn?

372
00:38:09,187 --> 00:38:11,608
What madness drove them in there?

373
00:38:29,508 --> 00:38:32,379
Did we lose him? I think we lost him.

374
00:38:39,284 --> 00:38:42,481
I'm going to rip out
your filthy little innards!

375
00:38:48,995 --> 00:38:49,943
Come here!

376
00:38:55,435 --> 00:38:57,955
Trees. Climb a tree.

377
00:39:07,314 --> 00:39:09,004
He's gone.

378
00:39:21,162 --> 00:39:23,365
Merry!

379
00:39:35,010 --> 00:39:39,166
Let's put a maggot hole in your belly!

380
00:39:46,454 --> 00:39:47,980
Run, Merry!

381
00:39:57,732 --> 00:40:02,008
Little Orcs.

382
00:40:02,336 --> 00:40:04,508
It's talking, Merry.
The tree is talking.

383
00:40:04,739 --> 00:40:06,594
Tree?

384
00:40:06,809 --> 00:40:09,678
I am no tree!

385
00:40:10,146 --> 00:40:12,217
I am an Ent.

386
00:40:12,781 --> 00:40:14,985
A tree-herder.

387
00:40:15,518 --> 00:40:17,404
A shepherd of the forest.

388
00:40:17,619 --> 00:40:19,048
Don't talk to it, Merry.

389
00:40:19,521 --> 00:40:21,015
Don't encourage it!

390
00:40:21,256 --> 00:40:25,282
Treebeard, some call me.

391
00:40:25,594 --> 00:40:27,482
And whose side are you on?

392
00:40:28,230 --> 00:40:29,691
Side?

393
00:40:30,099 --> 00:40:32,717
I am on nobody's side...

394
00:40:33,302 --> 00:40:38,353
...because nobody's on my side,
little Orc.

395
00:40:39,443 --> 00:40:43,915
Nobody cares for the woods anymore.

396
00:40:44,447 --> 00:40:46,684
We're not Orcs! We're Hobbits!

397
00:40:47,082 --> 00:40:49,220
Hobbits?

398
00:40:50,519 --> 00:40:55,222
Never heard of a Hobbit before.

399
00:40:56,593 --> 00:41:00,967
Sounds like Orc mischief to me!

400
00:41:01,332 --> 00:41:03,338
They come with fire.

401
00:41:03,600 --> 00:41:06,120
They come with axes.

402
00:41:06,403 --> 00:41:11,040
Gnawing, biting, breaking,
hacking, burning!

403
00:41:11,409 --> 00:41:15,085
- Destroyers and usurpers! Curse them!
- No!

404
00:41:15,412 --> 00:41:18,161
You don't understand. We're Hobbits!

405
00:41:18,448 --> 00:41:20,204
Halflings!

406
00:41:20,449 --> 00:41:21,497
Shire-folk!

407
00:41:21,685 --> 00:41:24,019
Maybe you are...

408
00:41:24,387 --> 00:41:27,933
...and maybe you aren't.

409
00:41:29,160 --> 00:41:32,934
The White Wizard will know.

410
00:41:33,763 --> 00:41:35,618
The White Wizard?

411
00:41:37,335 --> 00:41:38,676
Saruman.

412
00:41:51,382 --> 00:41:53,040
See? See?

413
00:41:53,316 --> 00:41:55,553
We've led you out.

414
00:41:55,786 --> 00:41:58,274
Hurry, Hobbitses. Hurry!

415
00:42:01,460 --> 00:42:03,881
Very lucky we find you.

416
00:42:10,568 --> 00:42:12,260
Nice Hobbit.

417
00:42:15,274 --> 00:42:18,371
It's a bog. He's led us into a swamp.

418
00:42:18,645 --> 00:42:21,229
A swamp, yes, yes.

419
00:42:22,113 --> 00:42:26,553
Come, master. We will take you
on safe paths through the mist.

420
00:42:29,155 --> 00:42:32,416
Come, Hobbits! Come! We go quickly.

421
00:42:35,761 --> 00:42:38,347
I found it. I did.

422
00:42:38,631 --> 00:42:41,215
The way through the marshes.

423
00:42:41,533 --> 00:42:44,949
Orcs don't use it.
Orcs don't know it.

424
00:42:45,271 --> 00:42:49,166
They go around for miles and miles.

425
00:42:49,509 --> 00:42:50,970
Come quickly.

426
00:42:51,210 --> 00:42:55,072
Soft and quick as shadows we must be.

427
00:42:56,381 --> 00:42:59,513
I hate this place. It's too quiet.

428
00:42:59,819 --> 00:43:02,088
There's been no sight nor sound
of a bird for two days.

429
00:43:02,323 --> 00:43:05,485
No, no birdses to eat.

430
00:43:05,992 --> 00:43:10,018
No crunchable birdses.

431
00:43:10,697 --> 00:43:13,479
We are famished! Yes!

432
00:43:13,733 --> 00:43:17,989
Famished we are, precious!

433
00:43:33,120 --> 00:43:34,494
Here.

434
00:43:35,723 --> 00:43:37,665
What does it eats?

435
00:43:38,058 --> 00:43:39,945
Is it tasty?

436
00:43:45,299 --> 00:43:47,689
It tries to chokes us!

437
00:43:48,203 --> 00:43:51,585
We can't eats Hobbit food!

438
00:43:53,508 --> 00:43:57,369
We must starve!

439
00:43:57,678 --> 00:44:00,045
Well, starve, then. And good riddance!

440
00:44:00,782 --> 00:44:03,019
Oh, cruel Hobbit.

441
00:44:03,251 --> 00:44:06,001
It does not care if we be hungry.

442
00:44:06,321 --> 00:44:10,892
Does not care if we should die.

443
00:44:11,626 --> 00:44:14,375
Not like master.

444
00:44:15,798 --> 00:44:17,969
Master cares.

445
00:44:19,200 --> 00:44:21,022
Master knows.

446
00:44:23,505 --> 00:44:25,393
Yes.

447
00:44:25,608 --> 00:44:28,193
Precious.

448
00:44:31,780 --> 00:44:35,326
Once it takes hold of us...

449
00:44:37,353 --> 00:44:41,346
...it never lets go.

450
00:44:42,258 --> 00:44:43,338
Don't touch me!

451
00:45:12,000 --> 00:45:30,000
<i><font color="#008000">♫ Ngyrth sí...</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(The dead...)</font></i>

452
00:45:15,759 --> 00:45:17,581
There are dead things!

453
00:45:17,795 --> 00:45:19,517
Dead faces in the water.

454
00:45:24,469 --> 00:45:28,265
All dead. All rotten.

455
00:45:29,039 --> 00:45:32,519
Elves and Men and Orcses.

456
00:45:33,043 --> 00:45:36,391
A great battle long ago.

457
00:45:37,381 --> 00:45:39,104
Dead Marshes.

458
00:45:39,350 --> 00:45:42,001
Yes. Yes, that is their name.

459
00:45:43,688 --> 00:45:45,410
This way.


460
00:45:45,623 --> 00:45:48,306
Don't follow the lights.

461
00:45:50,227 --> 00:45:53,470
Careful now! Or Hobbits go down
to join the dead ones...

462
00:45:53,650 --> 00:46:27,000
<i><font color="#008000">♫ Ngyrth sí ú-los[tar]</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(The dead do not sleep here)</font></i>

463
00:45:54,298 --> 00:45:58,192
...and light little candles
of their own.

464
00:46:24,530 --> 00:46:26,024
Frodo!

465
00:47:10,476 --> 00:47:15,016
- Gollum?
- Don't follow the lights.

466
00:47:15,349 --> 00:47:17,170
- Gollum!
- Mr. Frodo!

467
00:47:17,383 --> 00:47:19,205
Are you all right?

468
00:47:48,216 --> 00:47:51,062
So bright.

469
00:47:51,352 --> 00:47:55,029
So beautiful.

470
00:47:55,322 --> 00:47:59,032
Our precious.

471
00:48:00,595 --> 00:48:02,122
What did you say?

472
00:48:02,330 --> 00:48:04,370
Master should be resting.

473
00:48:04,599 --> 00:48:08,493
Master needs to keep up his strength.

474
00:48:10,638 --> 00:48:13,900
- Who are you?
- Mustn't ask us. Not its business.

475
00:48:14,174 --> 00:48:15,516
Gollum. Gollum.

476
00:48:15,744 --> 00:48:17,500
Gandalf told me you were
one of the river-folk.

477
00:48:17,713 --> 00:48:21,803
<i>Cold be heart and hand and bone
Cold be travelers far from home</i>

478
00:48:22,118 --> 00:48:23,524
He said your life was a sad story.

479
00:48:23,752 --> 00:48:28,159
<i>They do not see what lies ahead
When sun has failed and moon is dead</i>

480
00:48:28,523 --> 00:48:31,393
You were not so very different
from a Hobbit once.

481
00:48:31,661 --> 00:48:33,384
Were you?

482
00:48:35,631 --> 00:48:37,900
Sméagol.

483
00:48:42,604 --> 00:48:45,092
What did you call me?

484
00:48:46,510 --> 00:48:49,192
That was your name once, wasn't it?

485
00:48:49,779 --> 00:48:52,146
A long time ago.

486
00:48:53,115 --> 00:48:55,155
My name.

487
00:48:56,319 --> 00:48:57,661
My name.

488
00:49:04,594 --> 00:49:07,049
Sméagol.

489
00:49:11,268 --> 00:49:12,893
Black Riders!

490
00:49:13,102 --> 00:49:14,346
Hide! Hide!

491
00:49:25,048 --> 00:49:27,219
Come on, Frodo. Come on!

492
00:49:27,451 --> 00:49:30,996
Quick! They will see us!
They will see us!

493
00:49:31,788 --> 00:49:34,407
- I thought they were dead.
- Dead?

494
00:49:34,659 --> 00:49:37,473
No, you cannot kill them. No.

495
00:49:54,970 --> 00:49:58,459
<i><font color="#778899">♫ Nêbâbîtham Magânanê</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(We renounce our Maker)</font></i>

496
00:49:58,970 --> 00:50:03,459
<i><font color="#778899">♫ Nêtabdam dâur</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(We cling to the darkness)</font></i>

497
00:50:04,755 --> 00:50:05,966
Wraiths!

498
00:50:06,190 --> 00:50:08,263
Wraiths on wings!

499
00:50:16,334 --> 00:50:18,309
They are calling for it.

500
00:50:18,570 --> 00:50:22,018
They are calling for the precious.

501
00:50:24,270 --> 00:50:30,459
<i><font color="#778899">♫ Nênâkham</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(We are coming)</font></i>

502
00:50:24,308 --> 00:50:26,315
Mr. Frodo! It's all right.

503
00:50:26,545 --> 00:50:27,722
I'm here.

504
00:50:43,796 --> 00:50:45,356
Hurry, Hobbits.

505
00:50:45,865 --> 00:50:49,660
The Black Gate is very close.

506
00:50:56,708 --> 00:50:58,530
Orc blood.

507
00:51:08,555 --> 00:51:10,279
These are strange tracks.

508
00:51:11,592 --> 00:51:13,533
The air is so close in here.

509
00:51:14,761 --> 00:51:17,150
This forest is old.

510
00:51:18,098 --> 00:51:20,007
Very old.

511
00:51:21,734 --> 00:51:24,035
Full of memory...

512
00:51:26,673 --> 00:51:29,007
...and anger.

513
00:51:35,249 --> 00:51:38,063
The trees are speaking to each other.

514
00:51:38,318 --> 00:51:39,660
Gimli!

515
00:51:40,054 --> 00:51:41,744
Lower your ax.

516
00:51:44,658 --> 00:51:47,340
They have feelings, my friend.

517
00:51:48,094 --> 00:51:49,982
The Elves began it.

518
00:51:50,231 --> 00:51:54,638
Waking up the trees,
teaching them to speak.

519
00:51:55,436 --> 00:51:57,640
Talking trees.

520
00:51:58,441 --> 00:52:01,342
What do trees have to talk about?

521
00:52:01,610 --> 00:52:04,609
Except the consistency
of squirrel droppings.

522
00:52:07,383 --> 00:52:09,724
<font color="#008000">Aragorn, nad no ennas!</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(Aragorn, something’s out there!)</font>

523
00:52:16,000 --> 00:52:18,147
<font color="#008000">Man cenich?</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(What do you see?)</font>

524
00:52:18,727 --> 00:52:21,148
The White Wizard approaches.

525
00:52:27,403 --> 00:52:31,460
Do not let him speak.
He will put a spell on us.

526
00:52:41,316 --> 00:52:43,422
We must be quick.

527
00:52:59,168 --> 00:53:02,583
You are tracking the footsteps
of two young Hobbits.

528
00:53:03,340 --> 00:53:04,616
Where are they?

529
00:53:04,807 --> 00:53:08,287
They passed this way
the day before yesterday.

530
00:53:08,611 --> 00:53:12,636
They met someone they did not expect.

531
00:53:13,149 --> 00:53:15,157
Does that comfort you?

532
00:53:15,384 --> 00:53:17,272
Who are you?

533
00:53:18,755 --> 00:53:20,642
Show yourself!

534
00:53:29,632 --> 00:53:30,900
It cannot be.

535
00:53:31,100 --> 00:53:33,700
<i><font color="#800080">♫ Hwær cwóm helm? Hwær cwóm byrne?</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Where is the helm? Where is the hauberk?)</font></i>

536
00:53:34,100 --> 00:53:37,700
<i><font color="#800080">♫ Hwærcwóm feax flówende?</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Where is the bright hair flowing?)</font></i>

537
00:53:34,637 --> 00:53:35,565
Forgive me.

538
00:53:37,307 --> 00:53:38,194
I mistook you for Saruman.

539
00:53:38,200 --> 00:53:43,700
<i><font color="#800080">♫ Hwær cwóm hand on hearpestrenge?</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Where is the hand on the harp string?)</font></i>

540
00:53:40,180 --> 00:53:42,597
I am Saruman.

541
00:53:44,100 --> 00:53:49,700
<i><font color="#800080">♫ Hwær cwóm scir fýr scinende?</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Where is the red fire glowing?)</font></i>

542
00:53:44,347 --> 00:53:48,057
Or rather, Saruman
as he should have been.

543
00:53:49,219 --> 00:53:50,561
You fell.

544
00:53:52,189 --> 00:53:54,523
Through fire...

545
00:53:54,759 --> 00:53:56,133
...and water.

546
00:53:57,594 --> 00:54:00,081
<i>From the lowest dungeon
to the highest peak...</i>

547
00:54:00,331 --> 00:54:03,909
<i>...I fought with the Balrog
of Morgoth.</i>

548
00:54:19,785 --> 00:54:22,435
<i>U ntil at last I threw down
my enemy...</i>

549
00:54:22,687 --> 00:54:27,061
<i>...and smote his ruin
upon the mountainside.</i>

550
00:54:33,265 --> 00:54:35,632
Darkness took me...

551
00:54:36,535 --> 00:54:40,429
...and I strayed out of thought
and time.

552
00:54:41,406 --> 00:54:44,341
Stars wheeled overhead...

553
00:54:44,677 --> 00:54:49,084
...and every day was as long
as a life age of the Earth.

554
00:54:51,383 --> 00:54:53,390
But it was not the end.

555
00:54:53,719 --> 00:54:56,435
I felt life in me again.

556
00:54:58,525 --> 00:55:01,012
I've been sent back...

557
00:55:01,260 --> 00:55:02,667
...until my task is done.

558
00:55:03,195 --> 00:55:05,049
Gandalf.

559
00:55:05,698 --> 00:55:07,586
Gandalf?

560
00:55:08,201 --> 00:55:09,956
Yes.

561
00:55:12,672 --> 00:55:14,428
That was what they used to call me.

562
00:55:17,409 --> 00:55:19,514
Gandalf the Grey.

563
00:55:21,081 --> 00:55:22,641
That was my name.

564
00:55:23,017 --> 00:55:24,325
Gandalf.

565
00:55:26,354 --> 00:55:28,328
I am Gandalf the White.

566
00:55:31,459 --> 00:55:34,360
And I come back to you now...

567
00:55:34,661 --> 00:55:37,117
...at the turn of the tide.

568
00:55:38,332 --> 00:55:41,179
One stage of your journey is over.
Another begins.

569
00:55:42,103 --> 00:55:45,102
- We must travel to Edoras with all speed.
- Edoras?

570
00:55:46,173 --> 00:55:48,147
That is no short distance!

571
00:55:48,441 --> 00:55:51,507
We hear of trouble in Rohan.
It goes ill with the king.

572
00:55:51,778 --> 00:55:53,753
Yes, and it will not be easily cured.

573
00:55:54,181 --> 00:55:57,377
Then we have run all this way for nothing?

574
00:55:57,685 --> 00:55:59,572
Are we to leave those poor Hobbits here...

575
00:55:59,821 --> 00:56:03,943
...in this horrid, dark, dank,
tree-infested...?

576
00:56:06,627 --> 00:56:09,627
I mean, charming...

577
00:56:10,066 --> 00:56:12,585
...quite charming forest.

578
00:56:13,300 --> 00:56:16,878
It was more than mere chance that
brought Merry and Pippin to Fangorn.

579
00:56:17,100 --> 00:56:28,000
<i><font color="#800080">♫ Híe hine [sáwon] feorran</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(In the distance they saw him)</font></i>

580
00:56:17,171 --> 00:56:21,294
A great power has been sleeping here
for many long years.

581
00:56:21,609 --> 00:56:24,993
The coming of Merry and Pippin
will be like the falling of small stones...

582
00:56:25,281 --> 00:56:28,044
...that starts an avalanche
in the mountains.

583
00:56:28,800 --> 00:56:35,700
<i><font color="#800080">♫ And hwíte sun[nan in mane]</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(White sun caught in his mane)</font></i>

584
00:56:28,917 --> 00:56:31,586
In one thing you have not changed,
dear friend.

585
00:56:32,019 --> 00:56:35,368
You still speak in riddles.

586
00:56:36,100 --> 00:56:42,300
<i><font color="#800080">♫ [Híe lange hine] clipodon</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Long they called him)</font></i>

587
00:56:38,392 --> 00:56:44,470
A thing is about to happen that has not
happened since the Elder Days.

588
00:56:42,600 --> 00:56:48,700
<i><font color="#800080">♫ Ac hé [ne wolde cuman]</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(But he would not come)</font></i>

589
00:56:45,066 --> 00:56:48,415
The Ents are going to wake up...

590
00:56:49,204 --> 00:56:53,426
...and find that they are strong.
- Strong?!

591
00:56:54,444 --> 00:56:55,523
Oh, that's good.

592
00:56:55,711 --> 00:56:58,329
So stop your fretting, Master Dwarf.

593
00:56:59,549 --> 00:57:01,653
Merry and Pippin are quite safe.

594
00:57:02,050 --> 00:57:05,399
I n fact, they are far safer
than you are about to be.

595
00:57:05,688 --> 00:57:09,299
This new Gandalf's more grumpy
than the old one.

596
00:57:23,600 --> 00:57:46,500
<i><font color="#800080">♫ For ðon hé wæs Sceadufæx</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(For he was Shadowfax)</font></i>

597
00:57:31,715 --> 00:57:33,177
That is one of the Mearas...

598
00:57:33,383 --> 00:57:36,099
...unless my eyes are cheated
by some spell.

599
00:57:46,750 --> 00:57:56,700
<i><font color="#800080">♫ hláford ealra méara</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Lord of all Horses)</font></i>

600
00:57:53,770 --> 00:57:56,039
Shadowfax.

601
00:57:57,200 --> 00:58:07,700
<i><font color="#800080">♫ Anhé Neandé</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(And he answered only to one)</font></i>

602
00:57:58,609 --> 00:58:01,196
He is the lord of all horses...

603
00:58:02,813 --> 00:58:06,555
...and has been my friend
through many dangers.

604
00:58:21,100 --> 00:58:24,447
<i>O rowan mine</i>

605
00:58:24,736 --> 00:58:28,412
<i>I saw you shine</i>

606
00:58:28,739 --> 00:58:32,187
<i>U pon a summer's day</i>

607
00:58:33,411 --> 00:58:37,633
<i>U pon your head
How golden-red</i>

608
00:58:38,117 --> 00:58:42,556
<i>The crown you bore aloft</i>

609
00:58:43,053 --> 00:58:45,290
Such a beautiful verse.

610
00:58:45,523 --> 00:58:50,258
- Is it much further?
- Bru-ra-hroom. Don't be hasty.

611
00:58:50,596 --> 00:58:53,694
You might call it far, perhaps.

612
00:58:54,733 --> 00:58:58,409
My home lies deep in the forest...

613
00:58:58,737 --> 00:59:02,512
...near the roots of the mountain.

614
00:59:04,044 --> 00:59:07,458
I told Gandalf I would keep you safe.

615
00:59:07,780 --> 00:59:11,609
And safe is where I'll keep you.

616
00:59:12,151 --> 00:59:16,274
I believe you will enjoy this next one too.

617
00:59:16,788 --> 00:59:19,659
It's one of my own compositions.

618
00:59:20,126 --> 00:59:21,238
Right.

619
00:59:21,428 --> 00:59:27,276
<i>Beneath the roof of sleeping leaves</i>

620
00:59:27,702 --> 00:59:32,370
<i>And the dreams of trees unfold</i>

621
00:59:32,739 --> 00:59:39,002
<i>When woodland halls are green and cool</i>

622
00:59:39,413 --> 00:59:43,340
<i>And the wind is in the West</i>

623
00:59:44,050 --> 00:59:46,471
<i>Come back to me</i>

624
00:59:47,221 --> 00:59:51,443
<i>Come back to me</i>

625
00:59:51,759 --> 00:59:58,021
<i>And say my land is best</i>

626
01:00:05,673 --> 01:00:09,251
Sleep, little Shirelings.

627
01:00:09,543 --> 01:00:13,056
Heed no nightly noise.

628
01:00:13,347 --> 01:00:17,122
Sleep till morning light.

629
01:00:18,819 --> 01:00:22,943
I have business in the forest.

630
01:00:23,258 --> 01:00:28,472
There are many to call.
Many that must come.

631
01:00:30,064 --> 01:00:34,439
The Shadow lies on Fangorn.

632
01:00:34,769 --> 01:00:40,399
The withering of all woods
is drawing near.

633
01:00:50,185 --> 01:00:54,211
The veiling shadow that glowers
in the east takes shape.

634
01:00:55,224 --> 01:00:57,612
Sauron will suffer no rival.

635
01:00:58,260 --> 01:01:02,318
From the summit of Barad-dûr,
his Eye watches ceaselessly.

636
01:01:02,631 --> 01:01:05,947
But he is not so mighty yet
that he is above fear.

637
01:01:07,136 --> 01:01:09,024
Doubt ever gnaws at him.

638
01:01:09,239 --> 01:01:11,605
The rumor has reached him.

639
01:01:12,041 --> 01:01:14,724
The heir of Nûmenor still lives.

640
01:01:15,812 --> 01:01:18,562
Sauron fears you, Aragorn.

641
01:01:20,116 --> 01:01:22,188
He fears what you may become.

642
01:01:23,486 --> 01:01:26,682
And so he'll strike hard and fast
at the world of Men.

643
01:01:27,156 --> 01:01:30,505
He will use his puppet, Saruman,
to destroy Rohan.

644
01:01:30,828 --> 01:01:32,321
War is coming.

645
01:01:32,528 --> 01:01:36,041
Rohan must defend itself,
and therein lies our first challenge...

646
01:01:36,332 --> 01:01:38,601
...for Rohan is weak and ready to fall.

647
01:01:38,836 --> 01:01:42,413
The king's mind is enslaved,
it's an old device of Saruman's.

648
01:01:42,739 --> 01:01:45,674
His hold over King Théoden
is now very strong.

649
01:01:46,110 --> 01:01:50,517
Sauron and Saruman
are tightening the noose.

650
01:01:51,547 --> 01:01:53,587
But for all their cunning...

651
01:01:53,851 --> 01:01:56,372
...we have one advantage.

652
01:01:58,589 --> 01:02:01,109
The Ring remains hidden.

653
01:02:02,260 --> 01:02:04,081
And that we should seek to destroy it...

654
01:02:04,328 --> 01:02:07,175
...has not yet entered
their darkest dreams.

655
01:02:07,799 --> 01:02:11,059
And so the weapon of the enemy
is moving towards Mordor...

656
01:02:11,367 --> 01:02:12,710
...in the hands of a Hobbit.

657
01:02:13,071 --> 01:02:16,999
Each day brings it closer
to the fires of Mount Doom.

658
01:02:17,308 --> 01:02:19,728
We must trust now in Frodo.

659
01:02:20,145 --> 01:02:21,771
Everything depends upon speed...

660
01:02:22,147 --> 01:02:25,015
...and the secrecy of his quest.

661
01:02:27,117 --> 01:02:30,249
Do not regret your decision to leave him.

662
01:02:31,290 --> 01:02:33,972
Frodo must finish this task alone.

663
01:02:34,691 --> 01:02:37,058
He's not alone.

664
01:02:37,295 --> 01:02:38,788
Sam went with him.

665
01:02:39,597 --> 01:02:40,710
Did he?

666
01:02:41,065 --> 01:02:45,408
Did he, indeed? Good.

667
01:02:46,272 --> 01:02:48,540
Yes, very good.

668
01:02:56,648 --> 01:03:01,350
The Black Gate of Mordor.

669
01:03:04,323 --> 01:03:06,657
Oh, save us.

670
01:03:12,564 --> 01:03:15,631
My old Gaffer would have a thing or two
to say if he could see us now.

671
01:03:18,137 --> 01:03:22,327
Master says to show him
the way into Mordor.

672
01:03:22,676 --> 01:03:26,058
So good Sméagol does,
master says so.

673
01:03:26,345 --> 01:03:27,490
I did.

674
01:03:36,323 --> 01:03:38,264
That's it, then.

675
01:03:39,826 --> 01:03:41,167
We can't get past that.

676
01:04:26,373 --> 01:04:27,618
Look!

677
01:04:27,808 --> 01:04:29,302
The gate.

678
01:04:29,510 --> 01:04:30,622
It's opening!

679
01:04:38,186 --> 01:04:40,095
I can see a way down.

680
01:04:40,789 --> 01:04:42,960
Sam, no!

681
01:04:45,193 --> 01:04:46,437
Master!

682
01:06:10,348 --> 01:06:13,643
- I do not ask you to come with me, Sam.
- I know, Mr. Frodo.

683
01:06:14,586 --> 01:06:17,584
I doubt even these Elvish cloaks
will hide us in there.

684
01:06:18,256 --> 01:06:20,044
- Now!
- No!

685
01:06:20,624 --> 01:06:22,511
No! No, master!

686
01:06:22,760 --> 01:06:25,630
They catch you! They catch you!

687
01:06:27,165 --> 01:06:29,532
Don't take it to him.

688
01:06:32,570 --> 01:06:35,220
He wants the precious.

689
01:06:35,506 --> 01:06:38,375
Always he is looking for it.

690
01:06:38,676 --> 01:06:42,419
And the precious is wanting
to go back to him.

691
01:06:42,782 --> 01:06:46,555
But we mustn't let him have it.

692
01:06:53,191 --> 01:06:55,198
No! There's another way.

693
01:06:55,460 --> 01:06:58,046
More secret. A dark way.

694
01:06:58,431 --> 01:07:02,009
- Why haven't you spoken of this before?
- Because master did not ask.

695
01:07:02,535 --> 01:07:03,517
He's up to something.

696
01:07:04,236 --> 01:07:06,625
Are you saying there's another way
into Mordor?

697
01:07:07,039 --> 01:07:09,526
Yes. There's a path...

698
01:07:09,809 --> 01:07:12,265
...and some stairs.

699
01:07:12,546 --> 01:07:14,203
And then...

700
01:07:14,413 --> 01:07:17,577
...a tunnel.

701
01:07:31,698 --> 01:07:33,453
He's led us this far, Sam.

702
01:07:33,667 --> 01:07:35,095
Mr. Frodo, no.

703
01:07:36,303 --> 01:07:37,611
He's been true to his word.

704
01:07:42,576 --> 01:07:43,689
No.

705
01:07:46,046 --> 01:07:47,475
Lead the way, Sméagol.

706
01:07:48,248 --> 01:07:52,023
Good Sméagol always helps.

707
01:08:26,154 --> 01:08:27,102
Hello?

708
01:08:29,490 --> 01:08:31,465
Treebeard?

709
01:08:32,260 --> 01:08:33,537
Where has he gone?

710
01:08:33,729 --> 01:08:36,149
I had the loveliest dream last night.

711
01:08:36,797 --> 01:08:39,415
There was this large barrel,
full of pipe-weed.

712
01:08:39,667 --> 01:08:42,154
And we smoked all of it.
And then...

713
01:08:42,669 --> 01:08:44,557
...you were sick.

714
01:08:46,308 --> 01:08:49,058
I'd give anything for a whiff of Old Toby.

715
01:08:52,581 --> 01:08:54,468
Did you hear that?

716
01:09:01,622 --> 01:09:03,030
There it is again.

717
01:09:04,027 --> 01:09:08,369
Something's not right here.
Not right at all.

718
01:09:12,367 --> 01:09:15,181
You just said something... Treeish.

719
01:09:15,470 --> 01:09:19,267
No, I didn't. I was just stretching.

720
01:09:27,083 --> 01:09:28,741
You're taller.

721
01:09:29,419 --> 01:09:30,760
- Who?
- You!

722
01:09:31,153 --> 01:09:32,615
- Than what?
- Than me!

723
01:09:33,255 --> 01:09:35,295
I've always been taller than you.

724
01:09:35,525 --> 01:09:40,031
Pippin, everyone knows I'm the tall one.
You're the short one.

725
01:09:41,098 --> 01:09:42,472
Please, Merry.

726
01:09:42,665 --> 01:09:46,374
You're what? Three-foot-six? At the most?

727
01:09:47,170 --> 01:09:49,919
Whereas me, I'm pushing 3'7".

728
01:09:52,176 --> 01:09:54,280
3'8"!

729
01:09:56,347 --> 01:09:58,135
Three-foot-eight.

730
01:10:01,252 --> 01:10:03,106
You did something.

731
01:10:08,859 --> 01:10:10,452
Merry, don't! Don't drink it!

732
01:10:11,462 --> 01:10:12,803
Merry!

733
01:10:13,163 --> 01:10:15,367
No, Treebeard said that you
shouldn't have any.

734
01:10:15,599 --> 01:10:19,340
- I want some!
- It could well be dangerous!

735
01:10:19,670 --> 01:10:21,710
Give me it back. Merry!

736
01:10:23,674 --> 01:10:25,082
What's happening?!

737
01:10:25,876 --> 01:10:27,338
It's got my leg!

738
01:10:27,712 --> 01:10:29,205
Merry!

739
01:10:48,599 --> 01:10:50,225
Help!

740
01:10:56,908 --> 01:10:58,731
Away with you.

741
01:10:59,111 --> 01:11:00,703
You should not be waking.

742
01:11:01,379 --> 01:11:06,048
Eat earth. Dig deep. Drink water.

743
01:11:06,750 --> 01:11:09,272
Go to sleep.

744
01:11:09,689 --> 01:11:11,510
Away with you.

745
01:11:11,724 --> 01:11:14,985
Come, the forest is waking up.

746
01:11:15,628 --> 01:11:17,482
It isn't safe.

747
01:11:20,266 --> 01:11:24,041
The trees have grown wild
and dangerous.

748
01:11:24,338 --> 01:11:27,240
Anger festers in their hearts.

749
01:11:28,240 --> 01:11:29,701
Black are their thoughts.

750
01:11:30,077 --> 01:11:32,411
Strong is their hate.

751
01:11:32,679 --> 01:11:35,361
They will harm you if they can.

752
01:11:35,614 --> 01:11:39,094
There are too few of us now.

753
01:11:39,417 --> 01:11:43,215
Too few of us Ents left to manage them.

754
01:11:44,124 --> 01:11:46,513
Why are there so few of you
when you have lived so long?

755
01:11:46,793 --> 01:11:49,988
- Are there Ent children?
- Bru-ra-hroom.

756
01:11:50,262 --> 01:11:55,565
There have been no Entings
for a terrible long count of years.

757
01:11:56,103 --> 01:12:01,089
- Why is that?
- We lost the Entwives.

758
01:12:01,541 --> 01:12:02,817
Oh, I'm sorry.

759
01:12:03,110 --> 01:12:06,885
- How did they die?
- Die? No.

760
01:12:07,214 --> 01:12:10,246
We lost them.

761
01:12:10,549 --> 01:12:15,371
And now we cannot find them.

762
01:12:15,757 --> 01:12:21,833
I don't suppose you've seen Entwives
in the Shire?

763
01:12:22,262 --> 01:12:24,628
Can't say that I have.

764
01:12:25,299 --> 01:12:27,273
You, Pip?

765
01:12:28,736 --> 01:12:31,125
What do they look like?

766
01:12:33,608 --> 01:12:38,147
I don't remember now.

767
01:12:54,696 --> 01:12:58,470
Edoras and the Golden Hall
of Meduseld.

768
01:12:59,401 --> 01:13:02,019
There dwells Théoden, King of Rohan...

769
01:13:02,704 --> 01:13:05,453
...whose mind is overthrown.

770
01:13:05,707 --> 01:13:09,929
<i>Saruman 's hold over King Théoden
is now very strong.</i>

771
01:13:10,646 --> 01:13:13,645
My lord, your son...

772
01:13:14,082 --> 01:13:16,154
...he is dead.

773
01:13:17,686 --> 01:13:19,442
My lord?

774
01:13:20,756 --> 01:13:21,999
Uncle?

775
01:13:28,730 --> 01:13:31,000
Will you not go to him?

776
01:13:34,204 --> 01:13:36,440
Will you do nothing?

777
01:13:36,672 --> 01:13:38,582
Be careful what you say.

778
01:13:38,841 --> 01:13:41,045
Do not look for welcome here.

779
01:14:05,069 --> 01:14:09,029
Oh, he must have died
sometime in the night.

780
01:14:09,373 --> 01:14:11,413
What a tragedy for the king...

781
01:14:11,675 --> 01:14:14,521
...to lose his only son and heir.

782
01:14:15,745 --> 01:14:20,153
I understand.
His passing is hard to accept.

783
01:14:20,484 --> 01:14:25,218
Especially now that your brother
has deserted you.

784
01:14:25,556 --> 01:14:27,051
Leave me alone, snake!

785
01:14:28,492 --> 01:14:30,117
Oh, but you are alone.

786
01:14:31,729 --> 01:14:36,333
Who knows what you've spoken
to the darkness...

787
01:14:36,700 --> 01:14:40,048
...in the bitter watches of the night...

788
01:14:40,371 --> 01:14:43,949
...when all your life seems to shrink.

789
01:14:44,241 --> 01:14:48,234
The walls of your bower
closing in about you.

790
01:14:48,579 --> 01:14:53,019
A hutch to trammel some wild thing in.

791
01:14:55,420 --> 01:14:57,241
So fair.

792
01:14:58,556 --> 01:14:59,964
So cold.

793
01:15:01,793 --> 01:15:03,963
Like a morning of pale spring...

794
01:15:04,228 --> 01:15:07,458
...still clinging to winter's chill.

795
01:15:21,414 --> 01:15:23,715
Your words are poison.

796
01:16:56,378 --> 01:16:58,679
You'll find more cheer in a graveyard.

797
01:17:13,228 --> 01:17:16,905
I cannot allow you before Théoden King
so armed, Gandalf Greyhame.

798
01:17:18,467 --> 01:17:20,987
By order of Grima Wormtongue.

799
01:17:38,420 --> 01:17:40,144
Your staff.

800
01:17:43,560 --> 01:17:46,975
You would not part an old man
from his walking stick.

801
01:18:05,950 --> 01:18:08,568
My lord, Gandalf the Grey is coming.

802
01:18:17,093 --> 01:18:18,500
He's a herald of woe.

803
01:18:18,729 --> 01:18:23,071
The courtesy of your hall
is somewhat lessened of late...

804
01:18:24,335 --> 01:18:25,643
...Théoden King.

805
01:18:26,470 --> 01:18:28,957
He's not welcome.

806
01:18:30,007 --> 01:18:35,058
Why should I welcome you...

807
01:18:35,713 --> 01:18:39,258
...Gandalf Stormcrow?

808
01:18:39,550 --> 01:18:42,845
A just question, my liege.

809
01:18:43,221 --> 01:18:46,003
Late is the hour...

810
01:18:46,257 --> 01:18:50,053
...in which this conjurer
chooses to appear.

811
01:18:51,062 --> 01:18:53,036
Láthspell I name him.

812
01:18:53,264 --> 01:18:56,078
Ill news is an ill guest.

813
01:18:56,333 --> 01:19:00,609
Be silent. Keep your forked tongue
behind your teeth.

814
01:19:01,138 --> 01:19:02,928
I have not passed
through fire and death...

815
01:19:03,141 --> 01:19:06,207
...to bandy crooked words
with a witless worm.

816
01:19:07,312 --> 01:19:09,318
His staff.

817
01:19:09,581 --> 01:19:13,509
I told you to take the wizard's staff.

818
01:19:17,155 --> 01:19:19,010
Théoden...

819
01:19:19,558 --> 01:19:22,078
...son of Thengel...

820
01:19:24,029 --> 01:19:26,233
...too long have you sat
in the Shadows.

821
01:19:29,301 --> 01:19:32,400
I would stay still if I were you.

822
01:19:32,671 --> 01:19:34,646
Hearken to me!

823
01:19:40,313 --> 01:19:42,352
I release you...

824
01:19:42,615 --> 01:19:44,502
...from the spell.

825
01:19:56,230 --> 01:19:59,098
You have no power here...

826
01:19:59,399 --> 01:20:02,910
...Gandalf the Grey.

827
01:20:04,700 --> 01:20:10,700
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ Mettanna</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(To the end)</font></i>

828
01:20:08,442 --> 01:20:13,263
I will draw you, Saruman,
as poison is drawn from a wound.


829
01:20:13,500 --> 01:20:23,600
<i><font color="#800080">♫ Lim-strang wæs geboren</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Strong-limbed he was born)</font></i>

830
01:20:22,856 --> 01:20:23,800
Wait.

831
01:20:24,100 --> 01:20:32,700
<i><font color="#800080">♫ Bearn léod-cyninga</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(This son of Kings)</font></i>

832
01:20:25,826 --> 01:20:29,536
If I go, Théoden dies.

833
01:20:30,430 --> 01:20:32,502
You did not kill me...

834
01:20:33,000 --> 01:20:41,700
<i><font color="#800080">♫ Magorinc Mearces</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(This warrior of Rohan)</font></i>

835
01:20:33,066 --> 01:20:35,002
...you will not kill him.

836
01:20:38,840 --> 01:20:40,530
Rohan is mine.

837
01:20:42,100 --> 01:20:49,700
<i><font color="#800080">♫ Bunden in byrde tó lædenne</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Bound by birth to lead)</font></i>

838
01:20:42,175 --> 01:20:43,386
Be gone.

839
01:21:27,856 --> 01:21:30,027
I know your face.

840
01:21:34,596 --> 01:21:35,773
Éowyn.

841
01:21:38,267 --> 01:21:39,413
Éowyn.

842
01:21:47,711 --> 01:21:48,823
Gandalf?

843
01:21:49,511 --> 01:21:52,261
Breathe the free air again, my friend.

844
01:22:05,662 --> 01:22:08,214
Dark have been my dreams of late.

845
01:22:12,435 --> 01:22:16,079
Your fingers would remember
their old strength better...

846
01:22:16,407 --> 01:22:19,253
...if they grasped your sword.

847
01:23:04,455 --> 01:23:06,364
I've only...

848
01:23:06,590 --> 01:23:09,492
...ever served you, my lord.

849
01:23:09,795 --> 01:23:14,584
Your leechcraft would have had me
crawling on all fours like a beast!

850
01:23:15,802 --> 01:23:17,657
Send me not from your sight.

851
01:23:20,172 --> 01:23:22,660
No, my lord! No, my lord.

852
01:23:23,109 --> 01:23:24,221
Let him go.

853
01:23:24,876 --> 01:23:28,104
Enough blood has been spilt
on his account.

854
01:23:37,356 --> 01:23:39,526
Get out of my way!

855
01:23:41,828 --> 01:23:44,991
Hail, Théoden King!

856
01:24:09,622 --> 01:24:12,110
Where is Théodred?

857
01:24:15,228 --> 01:24:17,596
Where is my son?

858
01:25:05,800 --> 01:25:15,000
<i><font color="#800080">♫ Bealocwealm hafað fréone frecan forth onsended</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(An evil death has set forth the noble warrior)</font></i>

859
01:25:15,600 --> 01:25:22,000
<i><font color="#800080">♫ giedd sculon singan gléomenn sorgiende</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(A song shall sing sorrowing minstrels)</font></i>

860
01:25:22,700 --> 01:25:29,900
<i><font color="#800080">♫ on Meduselde þæt he ma no wære,</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(in Meduseld that he is no more,)</font></i>

861
01:25:30,600 --> 01:25:38,000
<i><font color="#800080">♫ his dryhtne dyrest and mæga deorost.</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(to his lord dearest and kinsmen most belover.)</font></i>

862
01:25:39,100 --> 01:25:41,700
<i><font color="#800080">♫ Bealo...</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(An evil death...)</font></i>

863
01:25:44,887 --> 01:25:46,577
<font color="#800080">Simbelmynë.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">("Evermind")</font>

864
01:25:51,793 --> 01:25:55,307
Ever has it grown on the tombs
of my forebearers.

865
01:25:59,336 --> 01:26:02,183
Now it shall cover the grave
of my son.

866
01:26:04,374 --> 01:26:08,084
Alas that these evil days
should be mine.

867
01:26:09,079 --> 01:26:13,235
The young perish and the old linger.

868
01:26:14,084 --> 01:26:16,058
That I should live...

869
01:26:16,286 --> 01:26:19,482
...to see the last days of my house.

870
01:26:20,789 --> 01:26:24,532
Théodred's death
was not of your making.

871
01:26:27,731 --> 01:26:31,080
No parent should have to bury
their child.

872
01:26:47,852 --> 01:26:49,673
He was strong in life.

873
01:26:50,100 --> 01:26:57,700
<i><font color="#800080">♫ Of cilde tó menn</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(From childhood to a man)</font></i>


874
01:26:50,821 --> 01:26:54,300
His spirit will find its way
to the halls of your fathers.

875
01:26:58,100 --> 01:27:23,700
<i><font color="#800080">♫ thæt hé his déath geséo</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(So that he might face his death)</font></i>

876
01:27:04,300 --> 01:27:12,000
<font color="#800080">Westu hál... Ferðu, Théodred, Ferðu.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(Be-thou well... Go-thou, Théodred, go-thou.)</font>

877
01:27:25,100 --> 01:27:33,700
<i><font color="#800080">♫ Thæt hearde sóth</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(The hard truth)</font></i>

878
01:27:39,138 --> 01:27:40,795
They had no warning.

879
01:27:41,206 --> 01:27:43,444
They were unarmed.

880
01:27:44,077 --> 01:27:47,939
Now the Wild Men are moving through
the Westfold, burning as they go.

881
01:27:49,082 --> 01:27:50,804
Rick, cot and tree.

882
01:27:51,284 --> 01:27:53,389
Where is Mama?

883
01:27:54,287 --> 01:27:58,313
This is but a taste of the terror
that Saruman will unleash.

884
01:27:58,659 --> 01:28:02,914
All the more potent for he is driven now
by fear of Sauron.

885
01:28:04,298 --> 01:28:07,167
Ride out and meet him head on.

886
01:28:08,069 --> 01:28:11,329
Draw him away from your women
and children.

887
01:28:11,939 --> 01:28:13,400
You must fight.

888
01:28:13,774 --> 01:28:17,319
You have 2000 good men riding north
as we speak.

889
01:28:17,777 --> 01:28:19,238
Éomer is loyal to you.

890
01:28:19,446 --> 01:28:22,097
His men will return
and fight for their king.

891
01:28:22,349 --> 01:28:26,122
They will be 300 leagues from here
by now.

892
01:28:29,990 --> 01:28:32,095
Éomer cannot help us.

893
01:28:32,860 --> 01:28:34,453
I know what it is you want of me...

894
01:28:34,861 --> 01:28:37,927
...but I will not bring further death
to my people.

895
01:28:39,799 --> 01:28:41,294
I will not risk open war.

896
01:28:43,571 --> 01:28:46,888
Open war is upon you,
whether you would risk it or not.

897
01:28:51,279 --> 01:28:52,871
When last I looked...

898
01:28:53,314 --> 01:28:56,859
...Théoden, not Aragorn,
was king of Rohan.

899
01:29:03,858 --> 01:29:05,997
Then what is the king's decision?

900
01:29:11,733 --> 01:29:12,943
By order of the king...

901
01:29:13,168 --> 01:29:14,476
...the city must empty.

902
01:29:15,871 --> 01:29:18,620
We make for the refuge of Helm's Deep.

903
01:29:19,007 --> 01:29:22,749
Do not burden yourself with treasures.
Take only what provisions you need.

904
01:29:23,078 --> 01:29:24,453
Helm's Deep.

905
01:29:24,813 --> 01:29:28,107
They flee to the mountains
when they should stand and fight.

906
01:29:28,415 --> 01:29:30,303
Who will defend them if not their king?

907
01:29:30,519 --> 01:29:32,975
He's only doing what he thinks
is best for his people.

908
01:29:33,222 --> 01:29:34,978
Helm's Deep has saved them
in the past.

909
01:29:35,191 --> 01:29:38,966
There is no way out of that ravine.
Théoden is walking into a trap.

910
01:29:39,262 --> 01:29:41,334
He thinks he's leading them to safety.

911
01:29:41,563 --> 01:29:43,767
What they will get is a massacre.

912
01:29:45,333 --> 01:29:47,788
Théoden has a strong will,
but I fear for him.

913
01:29:48,805 --> 01:29:51,935
I fear for the survival of Rohan.

914
01:29:52,475 --> 01:29:55,257
He will need you before the end,
Aragorn.

915
01:29:55,945 --> 01:29:58,465
The people of Rohan will need you.

916
01:29:59,081 --> 01:30:01,349
The defenses have to hold.

917
01:30:02,985 --> 01:30:04,709
They will hold.

918
01:30:08,792 --> 01:30:10,930
The Grey Pilgrim.

919
01:30:11,195 --> 01:30:13,748
That's what they used to call me.

920
01:30:14,030 --> 01:30:18,885
Three hundred lives of Men I've walked
this earth, and now I have no time.

921
01:30:20,604 --> 01:30:22,840
With luck, my search will not
be in vain.

922
01:30:23,407 --> 01:30:26,667
Look to my coming at first light
on the fifth day.

923
01:30:27,544 --> 01:30:30,161
At dawn, look to the east.

924
01:30:30,447 --> 01:30:32,008
Go.

925
01:30:59,344 --> 01:31:02,508
That horse is half mad, my lord.
There's nothing you can do. Leave him.

926
01:31:03,793 --> 01:31:05,878
<font color="#800080">Fæste.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(Fast.)</font>

927
01:31:07,000 --> 01:31:08,000
<font color="#800080">Stille nú.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(Be still now.)</font>

928
01:31:11,300 --> 01:31:12,900
<font color="#800080">Fæste.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(Fast.)</font>

929
01:31:15,200 --> 01:31:16,400
<font color="#800080">Stille.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(Be still.)</font>

930
01:31:21,000 --> 01:31:22,800
<font color="#800080">Stille.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(Be still.)</font>

931
01:31:25,000 --> 01:31:26,000
<font color="#800080">Stille.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(Be still.)</font>

932
01:31:27,900 --> 01:31:30,300
<font color="#800080">Lac is drefed, gefrægon.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(A battle is stirred up, they heard.)</font>

933
01:31:37,500 --> 01:31:40,000
<font color="#800080">Hwæt nemnað ðe?</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(What is your name?)</font>

934
01:31:41,854 --> 01:31:43,796
His name is Brego.

935
01:31:45,325 --> 01:31:47,146
He was my cousin's horse.

936
01:31:47,426 --> 01:31:49,182
Brego?.

937
01:31:49,900 --> 01:31:52,100
<font color="#800080">Ðin nama is cynglic.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(Your name is kingly.)</font>

938
01:31:54,300 --> 01:31:56,300
<font color="#008000">Man le trasta, Brego?</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(What troubles you, Brego?)</font>

939
01:32:01,400 --> 01:32:03,000
<font color="#008000">Man cenich?</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(What did you see?)</font>

940
01:32:04,010 --> 01:32:06,245
I have heard of the magic of Elves...

941
01:32:06,479 --> 01:32:09,774
...but I did not look for it
in a Ranger from the North.

942
01:32:10,950 --> 01:32:13,186
You speak as one of their own.

943
01:32:15,155 --> 01:32:17,391
I was raised in Rivendell...

944
01:32:17,891 --> 01:32:19,266
...for a time.

945
01:32:22,595 --> 01:32:24,700
Turn this fellow free.

946
01:32:25,332 --> 01:32:27,788
He's seen enough of war.

947
01:32:39,546 --> 01:32:42,329
Gandalf the White.

948
01:32:42,584 --> 01:32:44,950
Gandalf the Fool!

949
01:32:46,287 --> 01:32:50,148
Does he seek to humble me
with his newfound piety?

950
01:32:51,524 --> 01:32:55,321
There were three
who followed the wizard.

951
01:32:55,996 --> 01:33:01,047
An Elf, a Dwarf and a Man.

952
01:33:01,602 --> 01:33:04,220
You stink of horse.

953
01:33:09,577 --> 01:33:11,400
The Man...

954
01:33:13,515 --> 01:33:17,671
...was he from Gondor?
- No, from the North.

955
01:33:17,986 --> 01:33:21,662
One of the Dûnedain Rangers,
I thought he was.

956
01:33:21,990 --> 01:33:23,713
His cloth was poor.

957
01:33:24,558 --> 01:33:29,610
And yet he bore a strange ring.

958
01:33:30,933 --> 01:33:34,227
Two serpents with emerald eyes.

959
01:33:34,536 --> 01:33:40,165
One devouring,
the other crowned with golden flowers.

960
01:33:40,543 --> 01:33:42,364
The Ring of Barahir.

961
01:33:43,445 --> 01:33:46,926
So Gandalf Greyhame
thinks he has found Isildur's heir.

962
01:33:47,251 --> 01:33:50,382
The lost king of Gondor.
He is a fool.

963
01:33:50,820 --> 01:33:53,339
The line was broken years ago.

964
01:33:54,924 --> 01:33:56,298
It matters not.

965
01:33:56,526 --> 01:33:59,013
The world of Men shall fall.

966
01:33:59,261 --> 01:34:01,085
It will begin at Edoras.

967
01:34:10,273 --> 01:34:12,127
I am ready, Gamling.

968
01:34:12,375 --> 01:34:14,797
Bring my horse.

969
01:34:18,081 --> 01:34:19,325
This is not a defeat.

970
01:34:21,884 --> 01:34:23,029
We will return.

971
01:34:28,458 --> 01:34:30,847
We will return.

972
01:34:54,284 --> 01:34:56,171
You have some skill with a blade.

973
01:35:04,796 --> 01:35:06,770
Women of this country learned long ago:

974
01:35:06,998 --> 01:35:09,420
Those without swords
can still die upon them.

975
01:35:09,834 --> 01:35:11,459
I fear neither death nor pain.

976
01:35:12,904 --> 01:35:14,911
What do you fear, my lady?

977
01:35:18,343 --> 01:35:20,132
A cage.

978
01:35:21,446 --> 01:35:25,155
To stay behind bars until use
and old age accept them.

979
01:35:25,451 --> 01:35:29,225
And all chance of valor has gone
beyond recall or desire.

980
01:35:32,925 --> 01:35:34,833
You're a daughter of kings...

981
01:35:36,161 --> 01:35:39,292
...a shieldmaiden of Rohan.

982
01:35:44,836 --> 01:35:47,171
I do not think that would be your fate.

983
01:36:20,307 --> 01:36:23,176
Théoden will not stay at Edoras.

984
01:36:23,476 --> 01:36:25,451
It's vulnerable. He knows this.

985
01:36:25,879 --> 01:36:28,661
He will expect an attack on the city.

986
01:36:30,051 --> 01:36:33,116
They will flee to Helm's Deep...

987
01:36:33,420 --> 01:36:35,754
...the great fortress of Rohan.

988
01:36:37,023 --> 01:36:41,180
It is a dangerous road to take
through the mountains.

989
01:36:42,896 --> 01:36:44,423
They will be slow.

990
01:36:44,999 --> 01:36:49,189
They will have women and children
with them.

991
01:36:53,239 --> 01:36:55,379
Send out your Warg-riders.

992
01:37:10,324 --> 01:37:13,139
Hey, stinker, don't go getting
too far ahead.

993
01:37:13,395 --> 01:37:15,980
- Why do you do that?
- What?

994
01:37:16,263 --> 01:37:18,751
Call him names.
Run him down all the time.

995
01:37:19,234 --> 01:37:21,175
Because.

996
01:37:22,870 --> 01:37:24,877
Because that's what he is, Mr. Frodo.

997
01:37:25,140 --> 01:37:27,212
There's naught left in him
but lies and deceit.

998
01:37:27,844 --> 01:37:30,363
It's the Ring he wants.
It's all he cares about.

999
01:37:30,779 --> 01:37:32,917
You have no idea what it did to him...

1000
01:37:33,149 --> 01:37:35,449
...what it's still doing to him.

1001
01:37:37,919 --> 01:37:39,893
I want to help him, Sam.

1002
01:37:40,121 --> 01:37:41,299
Why?

1003
01:37:46,796 --> 01:37:49,762
Because I have to believe
he can come back.

1004
01:37:54,102 --> 01:37:55,956
You can't save him, Mr. Frodo.

1005
01:37:56,204 --> 01:37:58,856
What do you know about it?
Nothing!

1006
01:38:05,847 --> 01:38:09,840
I'm sorry, Sam. I don't know
why I said that.

1007
01:38:10,887 --> 01:38:11,967
I do.

1008
01:38:14,057 --> 01:38:15,846
It's the Ring.

1009
01:38:16,427 --> 01:38:17,953
You can't take your eyes off it.

1010
01:38:18,828 --> 01:38:20,716
I've seen you.

1011
01:38:21,198 --> 01:38:24,906
You're not eating. You barely sleep.

1012
01:38:26,870 --> 01:38:28,974
It's taken hold of you, Mr. Frodo.

1013
01:38:29,205 --> 01:38:31,857
- You have to fight it.
- I know what I have to do, Sam.

1014
01:38:32,109 --> 01:38:34,924
The Ring was entrusted to me.
It's my task.

1015
01:38:35,212 --> 01:38:36,902
Mine! My own!

1016
01:38:37,848 --> 01:38:39,855
Can't you hear yourself?

1017
01:38:40,084 --> 01:38:41,741
Don't you know who you sound like?

1018
01:38:52,063 --> 01:38:54,069
We wants it.

1019
01:38:54,298 --> 01:38:56,948
We needs it.

1020
01:38:57,201 --> 01:39:01,838
Must have the precious.

1021
01:39:02,206 --> 01:39:05,337
They stole it from us.

1022
01:39:05,810 --> 01:39:08,973
Sneaky little Hobbitses.

1023
01:39:09,246 --> 01:39:13,020
Wicked. Tricksy. False.

1024
01:39:13,317 --> 01:39:16,383
No. Not master.

1025
01:39:16,855 --> 01:39:20,400
Yes, precious. False.

1026
01:39:20,860 --> 01:39:25,082
They will cheat you, hurt you, lie!

1027
01:39:26,397 --> 01:39:28,818
Master's my friend.

1028
01:39:29,100 --> 01:39:33,922
You don't have any friends.
Nobody likes you.

1029
01:39:35,374 --> 01:39:37,829
Not listening. I'm not listening.

1030
01:39:38,110 --> 01:39:41,938
You're a liar and a thief.

1031
01:39:42,815 --> 01:39:44,222
No.

1032
01:39:45,216 --> 01:39:47,998
Murderer.

1033
01:39:50,523 --> 01:39:51,471
Go away.

1034
01:39:51,857 --> 01:39:54,061
Go away?

1035
01:39:56,162 --> 01:39:58,879
I hate you.

1036
01:39:59,131 --> 01:40:01,367
I hate you.

1037
01:40:01,901 --> 01:40:05,000
Where would you be without me?
Gollum. Gollum.

1038
01:40:05,304 --> 01:40:07,093
I saved us.

1039
01:40:07,307 --> 01:40:11,714
It was me. We survived because of me.

1040
01:40:13,079 --> 01:40:16,427
Not anymore.

1041
01:40:18,050 --> 01:40:19,457
What did you say?

1042
01:40:21,588 --> 01:40:25,296
Master looks after us now.

1043
01:40:25,592 --> 01:40:29,007
We don't need you.

1044
01:40:29,929 --> 01:40:31,337
What?

1045
01:40:31,531 --> 01:40:33,254
Leave now...

1046
01:40:33,500 --> 01:40:37,177
...and never come back.

1047
01:40:37,471 --> 01:40:38,419
No.

1048
01:40:39,073 --> 01:40:43,066
Leave now and never come back.

1049
01:40:45,913 --> 01:40:51,609
Leave now and never come back!

1050
01:41:03,797 --> 01:41:06,252
We told him to go away.

1051
01:41:06,499 --> 01:41:09,369
And away he goes, precious.

1052
01:41:09,805 --> 01:41:11,527
Gone! Gone! Gone!

1053
01:41:11,939 --> 01:41:13,727
Sméagol is free!

1054
01:41:18,545 --> 01:41:20,040
Look.

1055
01:41:20,248 --> 01:41:24,656
Look. See what Sméagol finds?

1056
01:41:34,296 --> 01:41:35,572
They are young.

1057
01:41:35,964 --> 01:41:38,297
They are tender. They are nice.

1058
01:41:38,532 --> 01:41:41,980
Yes, they are. Eat them. Eat them!

1059
01:41:44,907 --> 01:41:46,336
You'll make him sick, you will...

1060
01:41:47,576 --> 01:41:49,812
...behaving like that.

1061
01:41:52,247 --> 01:41:54,965
There's only one way to eat
a brace of coneys.

1062
01:41:59,255 --> 01:42:00,815
What's it doing?

1063
01:42:01,456 --> 01:42:04,009
Stupid, fat Hobbit.

1064
01:42:04,259 --> 01:42:06,331
It ruins it.

1065
01:42:06,595 --> 01:42:10,107
What's to ruin? There's hardly any meat
on them.

1066
01:42:14,404 --> 01:42:16,924
What we need is a few good taters.

1067
01:42:17,941 --> 01:42:20,842
What's taters, precious?

1068
01:42:21,144 --> 01:42:22,835
What's taters? Eh?

1069
01:42:23,046 --> 01:42:24,769
Po-ta-toes.

1070
01:42:25,114 --> 01:42:28,180
Boil them, mash them,
stick them in a stew.

1071
01:42:29,919 --> 01:42:35,101
Lovely, big, golden chips
with a nice piece of fried fish.

1072
01:42:36,592 --> 01:42:38,414
Even you couldn't say no to that.

1073
01:42:38,962 --> 01:42:41,001
Oh, yes, we could.

1074
01:42:41,263 --> 01:42:44,679
Spoil a nice fish.

1075
01:42:46,070 --> 01:42:48,491
Give it to us raw...

1076
01:42:48,905 --> 01:42:51,807
...and wriggling.

1077
01:42:52,076 --> 01:42:55,043
You keep nasty chips.

1078
01:42:56,146 --> 01:42:58,089
You're hopeless.

1079
01:43:10,594 --> 01:43:12,088
Mr. Frodo?

1080
01:43:30,082 --> 01:43:32,699
- Who are they?
- Wicked Men.

1081
01:43:32,951 --> 01:43:35,253
Servants of Sauron.

1082
01:43:36,188 --> 01:43:38,259
They are called to Mordor.

1083
01:43:38,489 --> 01:43:41,391
The Dark One is gathering all armies
to him.

1084
01:43:41,826 --> 01:43:44,825
It won't be long now.
He will soon be ready.

1085
01:43:46,465 --> 01:43:50,010
- Ready to do what?
- To make his war.

1086
01:43:50,336 --> 01:43:55,256
The last war that will cover
all the world in Shadow.

1087
01:43:55,874 --> 01:43:58,776
We've got to get moving. Come on, Sam.

1088
01:43:59,045 --> 01:44:00,190
Mr. Frodo.

1089
01:44:00,847 --> 01:44:02,275
Look.

1090
01:44:05,985 --> 01:44:08,156
It's an oliphaunt.

1091
01:44:16,429 --> 01:44:19,299
No one at home will believe this.

1092
01:44:30,576 --> 01:44:32,400
Sméagol?

1093
01:45:12,920 --> 01:45:15,221
We've lingered here too long.

1094
01:45:18,326 --> 01:45:19,536
Come on, Sam.

1095
01:45:33,174 --> 01:45:35,826
Wait! We're innocent travelers!

1096
01:45:37,513 --> 01:45:42,400
There are no travelers in this land.
Only servants of the Dark Tower.

1097
01:45:42,918 --> 01:45:45,732
We are bound to an errand of secrecy.

1098
01:45:47,156 --> 01:45:50,319
Those that claim to oppose the enemy
would do well not to hinder us.

1099
01:45:50,592 --> 01:45:52,730
The enemy?

1100
01:45:54,898 --> 01:45:58,158
His sense of duty was no less
than yours, I deem.

1101
01:46:00,836 --> 01:46:02,778
You wonder what his name is...

1102
01:46:04,307 --> 01:46:06,445
...where he came from.

1103
01:46:08,510 --> 01:46:10,932
And if he was really evil at heart.

1104
01:46:12,782 --> 01:46:16,010
What lies or threats led him
on this long march from home.

1105
01:46:17,853 --> 01:46:20,122
If he would not rather have stayed there...

1106
01:46:22,391 --> 01:46:23,920
...in peace.

1107
01:46:27,463 --> 01:46:30,365
War will make corpses of us all.

1108
01:46:30,800 --> 01:46:32,774
Bind their hands.

1109
01:46:38,945 --> 01:46:41,563
It's true, you don't see
many Dwarf women.

1110
01:46:41,848 --> 01:46:45,361
And in fact, they are so alike
in voice and appearance...

1111
01:46:45,685 --> 01:46:48,718
...that they're often mistaken
for Dwarf men.

1112
01:46:49,289 --> 01:46:51,111
It's the beards.

1113
01:46:51,391 --> 01:46:53,397
This, in turn, has given rise
to the belief...

1114
01:46:53,694 --> 01:46:56,443
...that there are no Dwarf women...

1115
01:46:56,730 --> 01:47:00,822
...and that Dwarves just spring out
of holes in the ground...

1116
01:47:02,669 --> 01:47:04,457
...which is, of course, ridiculous.

1117
01:47:10,644 --> 01:47:12,815
It's all right. Nobody panic.

1118
01:47:13,347 --> 01:47:15,322
That was deliberate.
It was deliberate.

1119
01:47:17,284 --> 01:47:20,929
I haven't seen my niece smile
for a long time.

1120
01:47:21,421 --> 01:47:24,040
She was a girl when they brought
her father back dead.

1121
01:47:24,359 --> 01:47:26,530
Cut down by Orcs.

1122
01:47:26,827 --> 01:47:29,676
She watched her mother
succumb to grief.

1123
01:47:30,431 --> 01:47:34,872
Then she was left alone,
to tend her king in growing fear.

1124
01:47:35,236 --> 01:47:39,611
Doomed to wait upon an old man,
who should have loved her as a father.

1125
01:47:49,785 --> 01:47:52,054
Gimli.

1126
01:47:52,354 --> 01:47:54,296
No, I couldn't.

1127
01:47:54,557 --> 01:47:56,344
I really couldn't.

1128
01:48:00,929 --> 01:48:02,457
I made some stew.

1129
01:48:02,731 --> 01:48:05,862
It isn't much, but it's hot.

1130
01:48:13,809 --> 01:48:15,783
Thank you.

1131
01:48:36,366 --> 01:48:38,787
- It's good.
- Really?

1132
01:48:42,872 --> 01:48:46,102
My uncle told me a strange thing.

1133
01:48:47,544 --> 01:48:51,439
He said that you rode to war
with Thengel, my grandfather.

1134
01:48:52,015 --> 01:48:54,382
But he must be mistaken.

1135
01:48:54,752 --> 01:48:58,975
King Théoden has a good memory.
He was only a small child at the time.

1136
01:49:00,324 --> 01:49:03,357
Then you must be at least 60.

1137
01:49:05,629 --> 01:49:07,091
Seventy?

1138
01:49:07,631 --> 01:49:09,225
But you cannot be 80!

1139
01:49:12,636 --> 01:49:13,946
Eighty-seven.

1140
01:49:17,108 --> 01:49:19,116
You are one of the Dûnedain.

1141
01:49:20,277 --> 01:49:23,245
A descendant of Nûmenor,
blessed with long life.

1142
01:49:24,583 --> 01:49:27,135
It was said that your race
had passed into legend.

1143
01:49:27,886 --> 01:49:29,576
There are few of us left.

1144
01:49:29,820 --> 01:49:32,471
The Northern Kingdom
was destroyed long ago.

1145
01:49:33,393 --> 01:49:36,621
I'm sorry. Please, eat.

1146
01:49:51,444 --> 01:49:55,404
<i>The light of the Evenstar
does not wax and wane.</i>

1147
01:49:56,349 --> 01:49:59,664
It is mine to give to whom I will.

1148
01:50:01,620 --> 01:50:03,922
Like my heart.

1149
01:50:05,491 --> 01:50:07,244
Go to sleep.

1150
01:50:07,460 --> 01:50:21,360
<i><font color="#008000">♫ Ú i vethed</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(This is not the end)</font></i>

1151
01:50:08,361 --> 01:50:10,728
I am asleep.

1152
01:50:17,336 --> 01:50:19,190
This is a dream.

1153
01:50:21,460 --> 01:50:36,560
<i><font color="#008000">♫ nâ i onnad</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(it is the beginning)</font></i>

1154
01:50:21,507 --> 01:50:24,573
Then it is a good dream.

1155
01:50:36,657 --> 01:50:38,665
Sleep.

1156
01:51:03,050 --> 01:51:05,932
<font color="#008000">Minlû pedich nin...</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(Once you told me...)</font>

1157
01:51:07,044 --> 01:51:09,230
<font color="#008000">i aur hen telitha.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(this day would come.)</font>

1158
01:51:11,025 --> 01:51:13,545
<font color="#008000">Ú i vethed ... nâ i onnad.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(This is not the end... it is the beginning.)</font>

1159
01:51:13,828 --> 01:51:15,900
<font color="#008000">Boe bedich go Frodo.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(You must go with Frodo.)</font>

1160
01:51:16,500 --> 01:51:18,650
<font color="#008000">Han bâd lîn.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(It is your path.)</font>

1161
01:51:29,000 --> 01:51:30,800
<font color="#008000">Dolen i vâd o nin.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(My path is hidden from me.)</font>

1162
01:51:32,548 --> 01:51:35,963
<font color="#008000">Si peliannen i vâd na dail lîn.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(It is already laid before your feet.)</font>

1163
01:51:36,500 --> 01:51:39,000
<font color="#008000">Si boe ú-dhannathach.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(You cannot falter now.)</font>

1164
01:51:41,725 --> 01:51:43,547
<font color="#008000">Arwen...</font>

1165
01:51:45,800 --> 01:51:48,800
<font color="#008000">Ae ú-esteliach nad...</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(If you trust nothing else...)</font>

1166
01:51:49,000 --> 01:51:51,000
<font color="#008000">estelio han...</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(trust in this...)</font>

1167
01:51:52,000 --> 01:51:54,500
<font color="#008000">estelio ammen.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(trust in us.)</font>

1168
01:52:04,460 --> 01:52:32,560
<i><font color="#008000">♫ Esteli o han...</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Trust this...)</font></i>

1169
01:52:33,111 --> 01:52:34,866
Where is she?

1170
01:52:36,113 --> 01:52:38,448
The woman who gave you that jewel.

1171
01:52:40,460 --> 01:52:52,560
<i><font color="#008000">♫ Estel, le iôn adar lín</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Hope, you are your father’s son)</font></i>

1172
01:52:41,853 --> 01:52:44,505
Our time here is ending.

1173
01:52:45,290 --> 01:52:47,745
Arwen's time is ending.

1174
01:52:48,594 --> 01:52:49,804
Let her go.

1175
01:52:50,027 --> 01:52:51,970
Let her take the ship into the west.

1176
01:52:52,263 --> 01:52:55,166
Let her bear away her love for you
to the Undying Lands.

1177
01:52:55,467 --> 01:52:57,223
There it will be ever green.

1178
01:52:58,803 --> 01:53:01,073
But never more than memory.

1179
01:53:02,441 --> 01:53:05,342
I will not leave my daughter here
to die.

1180
01:53:05,644 --> 01:53:09,125
- She stays because she still has hope.
- She stays for you.

1181
01:53:09,448 --> 01:53:11,652
She belongs with her people.

1182
01:53:23,800 --> 01:53:26,000
<font color="#008000">Nach gwannatha sin?</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(Are you going to leave in such way?)</font>

1183
01:53:27,300 --> 01:53:31,608
<font color="#008000">Ma nathach hi gwannathach or minuial archened?</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(Did you think you could slip away at first light - unnoticed?)</font>

1184
01:53:33,274 --> 01:53:35,000
<font color="#008000">Ú-ethelithon.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(I will not return.)</font>

1185
01:53:36,050 --> 01:53:38,000
<font color="#008000">Estelio guru lîn ne dagor.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(Trust in your skill in battle.)</font>

1186
01:53:38,478 --> 01:53:39,852
<font color="#008000">Ethelithach.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(You will come back.)</font>

1187
01:53:40,078 --> 01:53:42,053
<font color="#008000"> Ú-bedin o gurth ne dagor.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(I don’t speak about death in battle.)</font>

1188
01:53:42,315 --> 01:53:44,618
<font color="#008000">O man pedich?</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(What do you speak of?)</font>

1189
01:53:49,924 --> 01:53:52,989
<font color="#008000">Edra le men, men na guil edwen...</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(You have a chance for another life...)</font>

1190
01:53:54,995 --> 01:53:59,370
<font color="#008000">haer o auth a nîr a naeth.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(far from war and weeping and woe.)</font>

1191
01:54:00,066 --> 01:54:01,789
Why are you saying this?

1192
01:54:03,471 --> 01:54:06,503
I am mortal. You are Elf-kind.

1193
01:54:08,109 --> 01:54:10,661
It was a dream, Arwen.

1194
01:54:11,211 --> 01:54:12,521
Nothing more.

1195
01:54:13,949 --> 01:54:17,047
I don't believe you.

1196
01:54:26,161 --> 01:54:27,918
This belongs to you.

1197
01:54:30,764 --> 01:54:32,292
It was a gift.

1198
01:54:34,970 --> 01:54:36,400
Keep it.

1199
01:54:39,007 --> 01:54:40,152
My lord?

1200
01:54:43,011 --> 01:54:47,387
She is sailing to the Undying Lands
with all that is left of her kin.

1201
01:55:11,074 --> 01:55:12,448
What is it?

1202
01:55:14,044 --> 01:55:16,018
- Háma?
- I'm not sure.

1203
01:55:32,596 --> 01:55:34,571
Wargs!

1204
01:55:47,211 --> 01:55:48,837
A scout!

1205
01:55:55,219 --> 01:55:57,641
- What is it? What do you see?
- Warg! We're under attack!

1206
01:55:59,089 --> 01:56:01,194
Get them out of here!

1207
01:56:06,030 --> 01:56:07,972
All riders to the head of the column.

1208
01:56:08,767 --> 01:56:10,676
Come on. Get me up here. I'm a rider.

1209
01:56:10,936 --> 01:56:12,594
Come on!

1210
01:56:24,516 --> 01:56:26,850
You must lead the people
to Helm's Deep, and make haste.

1211
01:56:27,152 --> 01:56:28,558
- I can fight.
- No!

1212
01:56:31,323 --> 01:56:33,298
You must do this, for me.

1213
01:56:35,395 --> 01:56:36,921
Follow me!

1214
01:56:40,500 --> 01:56:44,624
- Forward. I mean, charge forward.
- Make for the lower ground!

1215
01:56:44,900 --> 01:56:53,200
<i><font color="#800080">♫ Hwær cwóm hearpestrenge?</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Where is the harp string?)</font></i>

1216
01:56:45,004 --> 01:56:47,557
- That's it! Go on!
- Stay together!

1217
01:56:53,400 --> 01:57:03,700
<i><font color="#800080">♫ Hwær cwóm scir fýr scinende?</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Where is the red fire glowing?)</font></i>

1218
01:57:23,100 --> 01:57:31,700
<i><font color="#800080">♫ Hwær cwóm helm?</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Where is the helm?)</font></i>

1219
01:57:59,914 --> 01:58:02,119
Bring your pretty face to my ax.

1220
01:58:05,020 --> 01:58:06,482
That one counts as mine!

1221
01:58:23,272 --> 01:58:24,832
Stinking creature.

1222
01:59:52,131 --> 01:59:53,954
Aragorn!

1223
01:59:58,738 --> 02:00:00,145
Aragorn?

1224
02:00:14,220 --> 02:00:17,034
Tell me what happened
and I will ease your passing.

1225
02:00:17,323 --> 02:00:18,698
He's...

1226
02:00:19,325 --> 02:00:20,852
...dead.

1227
02:00:21,561 --> 02:00:24,343
He took a little tumble off the cliff.

1228
02:00:28,068 --> 02:00:29,312
You lie.

1229
02:01:03,271 --> 02:01:04,796
Get the wounded on horses.

1230
02:01:06,174 --> 02:01:09,206
The wolves of Isengard will return.

1231
02:01:09,744 --> 02:01:11,785
Leave the dead.

1232
02:01:19,321 --> 02:01:20,728
Come.

1233
02:01:30,999 --> 02:01:32,461
- At last!
- Helm's Deep.

1234
02:01:32,701 --> 02:01:35,484
There it is, Helm's Deep.

1235
02:01:38,139 --> 02:01:39,896
We're safe!

1236
02:01:41,476 --> 02:01:44,226
We're safe, my lady.

1237
02:01:44,514 --> 02:01:45,659
Thank you.

1238
02:02:30,127 --> 02:02:31,469
- Mama!
- Éothain!

1239
02:02:31,695 --> 02:02:33,124
Freda!

1240
02:02:38,936 --> 02:02:41,654
- Where is the rest?
- This is all we could save, my lady.

1241
02:02:45,610 --> 02:02:46,886
Take it to the caves.

1242
02:02:47,110 --> 02:02:49,827
Make way for the king.

1243
02:02:51,815 --> 02:02:54,663
Make way for Théoden.
Make way for the king.

1244
02:03:02,727 --> 02:03:06,305
So few. So few of you have returned.

1245
02:03:09,235 --> 02:03:11,406
Our people are safe.

1246
02:03:12,837 --> 02:03:15,294
We have paid for it with many lives.

1247
02:03:16,241 --> 02:03:17,703
My lady.

1248
02:03:21,480 --> 02:03:23,651
Lord Aragorn...

1249
02:03:23,916 --> 02:03:25,094
...where is he?

1250
02:03:27,186 --> 02:03:28,615
He fell.

1251
02:03:33,100 --> 02:03:40,700
<i><font color="#800080">♫ Héo dréag thá losinga</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(She felt the loss)</font></i>

1252
02:03:41,100 --> 02:03:51,400
<i><font color="#800080">♫ Earla thinga the héo forléas</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Of everything that had been missed)</font></i>

1253
02:03:51,744 --> 02:03:54,191
Draw all our forces behind the wall.

1254
02:03:54,481 --> 02:03:57,296
Bar the gate.
And set a watch on the surround.

1255
02:03:57,651 --> 02:04:00,619
What of those who cannot fight, my lord?
The women and children?

1256
02:04:00,922 --> 02:04:03,409
Get them into the caves.

1257
02:04:04,423 --> 02:04:09,094
Saruman's arm will have grown long
indeed if he thinks he can reach us here.

1258
02:04:11,331 --> 02:04:14,592
Helm 's Deep has one weakness.

1259
02:04:14,902 --> 02:04:17,138
Its outer wall is solid rock...

1260
02:04:17,404 --> 02:04:20,373
...but for a small culvert
at its base...

1261
02:04:20,675 --> 02:04:23,325
...which is little more than a drain.

1262
02:04:26,280 --> 02:04:30,274
How? How can fire undo stone?

1263
02:04:30,619 --> 02:04:34,929
What kind of device
could bring down the wall?

1264
02:04:38,760 --> 02:04:42,555
If the wall is breached,
Helm's Deep will fall.

1265
02:04:42,931 --> 02:04:46,313
Even if it is breached, it would take
a number beyond reckoning...

1266
02:04:46,634 --> 02:04:49,090
...thousands, to storm the Keep.

1267
02:04:49,371 --> 02:04:50,745
Tens of thousands.

1268
02:04:50,973 --> 02:04:54,868
But, my lord, there is no such force.

1269
02:04:57,080 --> 02:05:06,200
<font color="#FF0000">Durbgu Nazg-shu, Durbgu Dash-shu</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(Lord of the Ring, Lord of the Earth)</font>

1270
02:05:06,954 --> 02:05:09,923
A new power is rising.

1271
02:05:10,259 --> 02:05:13,106
Its victory is at hand.

1272
02:05:18,935 --> 02:05:20,908
This night...

1273
02:05:21,438 --> 02:05:25,594
...the land will be stained
with the blood of Rohan!

1274
02:05:25,941 --> 02:05:29,138
March to Helm's Deep!

1275
02:05:29,445 --> 02:05:32,741
Leave none alive!

1276
02:05:35,385 --> 02:05:37,774
To war!

1277
02:05:41,792 --> 02:05:46,070
There will be no dawn for Men.

1278
02:06:03,479 --> 02:06:05,454
Look. There's smoke to the south.

1279
02:06:05,716 --> 02:06:08,750
There is always smoke rising...

1280
02:06:09,087 --> 02:06:12,763
...from Isengard these days.

1281
02:06:13,190 --> 02:06:14,684
Isengard?

1282
02:06:14,993 --> 02:06:16,748
There was a time...

1283
02:06:17,195 --> 02:06:20,543
...when Saruman would walk in my woods.

1284
02:06:20,898 --> 02:06:24,128
But now he has a mind of metal...

1285
02:06:24,937 --> 02:06:27,270
...and wheels.

1286
02:06:28,139 --> 02:06:32,449
He no longer cares for growing things.

1287
02:06:32,811 --> 02:06:34,534
What is it?

1288
02:06:39,584 --> 02:06:41,722
It's Saruman's army.

1289
02:06:41,987 --> 02:06:43,480
The war has started.

1290
02:06:58,970 --> 02:07:12,259
<i><font color="#008000">♫ Uich gwennen na 'wanath ah na dhín</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(You are not bound to loss and silence)</font></i>

1291
02:07:12,970 --> 02:07:16,559
<i><font color="#008000">♫ An uich gwennen na</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(For you are not bound)</font></i>

1292
02:07:16,970 --> 02:07:25,259
<i><font color="#008000">♫ Boe naid bain gwannathar</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(All things must pass away)</font></i>

1293
02:07:21,894 --> 02:07:25,417
May the grace of the Valar protect you.

1294
02:07:25,670 --> 02:07:40,259
<i><font color="#008000">♫ Boe cuil ban firitha</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(All life is doomed to fade)</font></i>


1295
02:07:58,534 --> 02:08:00,355
Brego.

1296
02:08:26,562 --> 02:08:27,675
<font color="#008000">Arwen.</font>

1297
02:08:29,097 --> 02:08:30,885
<font color="#008000">Tollen i lû.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(It is time.)</font>

1298
02:08:32,969 --> 02:08:36,679
<font color="#008000">I chair gwannar na Valannor. Si bado, no círar.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(The ships depart to Valinor. Now go, before they sail.)</font>

1299
02:08:37,540 --> 02:08:39,263
I have made my choice.

1300
02:08:45,783 --> 02:08:48,532
He is not coming back.

1301
02:08:50,086 --> 02:08:53,282
Why do you linger here
when there is no hope?

1302
02:08:54,324 --> 02:08:57,194
There is still hope.

1303
02:09:01,498 --> 02:09:05,110
If Aragorn survives this war,
you will still be parted.

1304
02:09:08,672 --> 02:09:11,519
If Sauron is defeated
and Aragorn made king...

1305
02:09:11,808 --> 02:09:14,198
...and all that you hope for
comes true...

1306
02:09:14,477 --> 02:09:18,985
...you will still have to taste
the bitterness of mortality.

1307
02:09:19,450 --> 02:09:22,319
Whether by the sword
or the slow decay of time...

1308
02:09:22,620 --> 02:09:25,435
...Aragorn will die.

1309
02:09:26,970 --> 02:09:34,259
<i><font color="#008000">♫ Úivethed nâ i onnad</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(This is not the end, it is the beginning)</font></i>

1310
02:09:28,393 --> 02:09:30,848
And there will be no comfort
for you...

1311
02:09:31,129 --> 02:09:35,122
...no comfort to ease the pain
of his passing.

1312
02:09:34,970 --> 02:09:40,259
<i><font color="#008000">♫ Si boe ú-dhanna</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(You must not falter now)</font></i>

1313
02:09:38,136 --> 02:09:40,721
He will come to death...

1314
02:09:41,500 --> 02:09:56,259
<i><font color="#008000">♫ Ae ú-esteli, esteliach nad...</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(If you trust nothing else...)</font></i>

1315
02:09:41,510 --> 02:09:43,494
...an image of the splendor
of the kings of Men...

1316
02:09:43,807 --> 02:09:48,281
...in glory undimmed before
the breaking of the world.

1317
02:09:57,700 --> 02:10:13,259
<i><font color="#008000">♫ Estelio han, estelio han, estelio</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Trust this, trust this, trust)</font></i>

1318
02:09:57,755 --> 02:10:01,352
But you, my daughter...

1319
02:10:02,328 --> 02:10:07,150
...you will linger on in darkness
and in doubt...

1320
02:10:07,532 --> 02:10:11,427
...as nightfall in winter
that comes without a star.

1321
02:10:13,970 --> 02:10:29,259
<i><font color="#008000">♫ Estelio han, estelio veleth</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Trust this, trust love)</font></i>

1322
02:10:14,040 --> 02:10:16,342
Here you will dwell...

1323
02:10:16,609 --> 02:10:21,311
...bound to your grief
under the fading trees...

1324
02:10:23,249 --> 02:10:25,159
...until all the world is changed...

1325
02:10:25,418 --> 02:10:29,728
...and the long years of your life
are utterly spent.

1326
02:10:34,970 --> 02:10:44,259
<i><font color="#008000">♫ Estel, le iôn adar lín</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Hope, you are your father’s son)</font></i>

1327
02:10:38,431 --> 02:10:39,511
Arwen.

1328
02:10:46,238 --> 02:10:48,409
There is nothing for you here...

1329
02:10:49,177 --> 02:10:51,184
...only death.

1330
02:11:12,065 --> 02:11:15,099
<font color="#008000">Ah im, ú-’erin veleth lîn?</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">Do I not also have your love?</font>

1331
02:11:16,804 --> 02:11:18,496
<font color="#008000">Gerich veleth nîn, ada.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">You have my love, father.</font>

1332
02:11:25,970 --> 02:11:41,259
<i><font color="#008000">♫ Nef Elbereth Gil[thoniel]</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Heavenly Elbereth Kindler of Stars)</font></i>

1333
02:11:43,970 --> 02:12:03,259
<i><font color="#008000">♫ Boe naer, [an]nant ui[ch] ben-estel</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Sorrowing, and yet you are not without hope)</font></i>

1334
02:12:06,970 --> 02:12:17,259
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ Man ammen toltha i dann hen môrn?</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Who brings to us this token of darkness?)</font></i>

1335
02:12:09,750 --> 02:12:12,750
<font color="#008000">I amar prestar aen,</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(The world is changed,)</font>

1336
02:12:13,400 --> 02:12:15,400
<font color="#008000">han mathon ne nen,</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(I feel it in the water.)</font>

1337
02:12:15,950 --> 02:12:17,950
<font color="#008000">han mathon ne chae,</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(I feel it in the earth,)</font>

1338
02:12:19,740 --> 02:12:27,259
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ Si danna atha nauva</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Now all will fall away)</font></i>

1339
02:12:19,750 --> 02:12:23,520
<font color="#008000">a han noston ned ’wilith.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(I smell it in the air.)</font>

1340
02:12:24,707 --> 02:12:28,220
The power of the enemy is growing.

1341
02:12:28,546 --> 02:12:31,066
Sauron will use his puppet,
Saruman...

1342
02:12:31,347 --> 02:12:34,577
...to destroy the people of Rohan.

1343
02:12:36,740 --> 02:12:44,259
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ Mel, melmë nóren sina</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Love, our love for this land)</font></i>

1344
02:12:36,786 --> 02:12:40,267
Isengard has been unleashed.

1345
02:12:44,728 --> 02:12:47,958
The Eye of Sauron now turns
to Gondor...

1346
02:12:49,140 --> 02:13:00,259
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ Nur ala aëaron</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(is deeper than the depths of the sea)</font></i>

1347
02:12:49,233 --> 02:12:52,103
...the last free kingdom of Men.

1348
02:12:52,436 --> 02:12:56,625
His war on this country
will come swiftly.

1349
02:13:00,540 --> 02:13:14,259
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ Nuruva Tercáno</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(The Herald of Death)</font></i>

1350
02:13:00,544 --> 02:13:03,479
He senses the Ring is close.

1351
02:13:03,815 --> 02:13:07,131
The strength of the Ring-bearer
is failing.

1352
02:13:07,451 --> 02:13:11,347
In his heart, Frodo begins
to understand...

1353
02:13:13,058 --> 02:13:16,767
...the quest will claim his life.

1354
02:13:17,094 --> 02:13:19,167
You know this.

1355
02:13:19,865 --> 02:13:22,582
You have foreseen it.

1356
02:13:24,803 --> 02:13:28,119
It is the risk we all took.

1357
02:13:32,611 --> 02:13:36,637
In the gathering dark, the will
of the Ring grows strong.

1358
02:13:37,984 --> 02:13:42,239
It works hard now to find its way back
into the hands of Men.

1359
02:13:42,588 --> 02:13:47,825
Men, who are so easily seduced
by its power.

1360
02:13:48,260 --> 02:13:51,676
The young captain of Gondor
has but to extend his hand...

1361
02:13:51,999 --> 02:13:55,927
...take the Ring for his own,
and the world will fall.

1362
02:13:58,504 --> 02:14:00,261
It is close now.

1363
02:14:00,507 --> 02:14:04,598
So close to achieving its goal.

1364
02:14:07,915 --> 02:14:11,363
For Sauron will have dominion
over all life on this Earth...

1365
02:14:11,717 --> 02:14:15,679
...even unto to the ending
of the world.

1366
02:14:17,691 --> 02:14:19,447
The time of the Elves...

1367
02:14:19,726 --> 02:14:21,581
...is over.

1368
02:14:22,497 --> 02:14:25,943
Do we leave Middle-earth
to its fate?

1369
02:14:28,036 --> 02:14:31,166
Do we let them stand alone?

1370
02:14:35,842 --> 02:14:37,185
What news?

1371
02:14:37,412 --> 02:14:40,094
Our scouts report Saruman
has attacked Rohan.

1372
02:14:40,381 --> 02:14:43,131
Théoden's people have fled
to Helm's Deep.

1373
02:14:43,418 --> 02:14:47,280
But we must look to our own borders.
Faramir, Orcs are on the move.

1374
02:14:47,623 --> 02:14:49,924
Sauron is marshaling an army.

1375
02:14:50,358 --> 02:14:52,399
Easterlings and Southrons
are at the Black Gate.

1376
02:14:52,660 --> 02:14:55,922
- How many?
- Some thousands. More come every day.

1377
02:14:57,166 --> 02:15:00,582
- Who's covering the river to the north?
- We pulled 500 men at Osgiliath.

1378
02:15:00,903 --> 02:15:03,837
If their city is attacked,
we won't hold it.

1379
02:15:06,075 --> 02:15:08,180
Saruman attacks from Isengard.

1380
02:15:08,476 --> 02:15:11,030
Sauron from Mordor.

1381
02:15:12,481 --> 02:15:15,547
The fight will come to Men
on both fronts.

1382
02:15:15,884 --> 02:15:17,477
Gondor is weak.

1383
02:15:17,753 --> 02:15:20,753
Sauron will strike us soon.

1384
02:15:21,624 --> 02:15:23,413
And he will strike hard.

1385
02:15:23,926 --> 02:15:27,854
He knows now we do not have
the strength to repel him.

1386
02:15:41,878 --> 02:15:44,017
My men tell me that you are Orc spies.

1387
02:15:44,315 --> 02:15:46,900
Spies? Now wait just a minute.

1388
02:15:47,216 --> 02:15:49,388
Well, if you're not spies,
then who are you?

1389
02:15:56,359 --> 02:15:58,018
Speak.

1390
02:15:59,196 --> 02:16:01,683
We are Hobbits of the Shire.

1391
02:16:02,133 --> 02:16:05,035
Frodo Baggins is my name,
and this is Samwise Gamgee.

1392
02:16:05,568 --> 02:16:07,030
Your bodyguard?

1393
02:16:07,271 --> 02:16:08,994
His gardener.

1394
02:16:09,674 --> 02:16:11,584
And where is your skulking friend?

1395
02:16:13,177 --> 02:16:15,413
That gangrel creature.

1396
02:16:15,812 --> 02:16:17,701
He had an ill-favored look.

1397
02:16:19,517 --> 02:16:21,372
There was no other.

1398
02:16:25,555 --> 02:16:27,792
We set out from Rivendell
with seven companions.

1399
02:16:31,229 --> 02:16:34,163
One we lost in Moria...

1400
02:16:35,367 --> 02:16:36,828
...two were my kin...

1401
02:16:37,068 --> 02:16:40,647
...a Dwarf there was also.
And an Elf and two Men.

1402
02:16:40,972 --> 02:16:44,715
Aragorn, son of Arathorn,
and Boromir of Gondor.

1403
02:16:49,881 --> 02:16:51,572
You're a friend of Boromir?

1404
02:16:54,119 --> 02:16:55,527
Yes.

1405
02:16:56,688 --> 02:16:57,703
For my part.

1406
02:17:04,298 --> 02:17:07,112
It will grieve you then to learn
that he is dead.

1407
02:17:09,268 --> 02:17:10,674
Dead?

1408
02:17:10,903 --> 02:17:12,876
How? When?

1409
02:17:13,207 --> 02:17:15,759
As one of his companions,
I'd hoped you would tell me.

1410
02:17:16,175 --> 02:17:19,852
If something has happened to Boromir,
we would have you tell us.

1411
02:17:22,750 --> 02:17:28,947
His horn washed up upon the riverbank,
about six days past.

1412
02:17:29,456 --> 02:17:32,423
It was cloven in two.

1413
02:17:34,160 --> 02:17:37,422
But more than this, I know it in my heart.

1414
02:17:39,599 --> 02:17:41,323
He was my brother.

1415
02:18:30,352 --> 02:18:33,166
Boromir!

1416
02:18:33,855 --> 02:18:35,644
Boromir!

1417
02:18:39,961 --> 02:18:43,574
This city was once the jewel
of our kingdom.

1418
02:18:43,900 --> 02:18:47,412
A place of light and beauty and music.

1419
02:18:47,736 --> 02:18:49,973
And so it shall be once more!

1420
02:18:52,608 --> 02:18:55,162
Let the armies of Mordor know this:

1421
02:18:55,444 --> 02:18:59,635
Never again will the land of my people
fall into enemy hands.

1422
02:19:03,620 --> 02:19:09,086
This city of Osgiliath
has been reclaimed for Gondor!

1423
02:19:09,693 --> 02:19:11,580
- For Gondor!
- For Gondor!

1424
02:19:11,828 --> 02:19:14,545
- For Gondor!
- For Gondor!

1425
02:19:23,373 --> 02:19:26,025
Good speech. Nice and short.

1426
02:19:26,311 --> 02:19:29,092
Leaves more time for drinking!

1427
02:19:29,513 --> 02:19:33,540
Break out the ale! These men are thirsty!

1428
02:19:37,188 --> 02:19:39,228
Remember today, little brother.

1429
02:19:39,524 --> 02:19:42,393
Today, life is good.

1430
02:19:46,697 --> 02:19:48,224
What?

1431
02:19:48,667 --> 02:19:50,074
He's here.

1432
02:19:53,337 --> 02:19:54,899
One moment of peace,
can he not give us that?

1433
02:19:55,140 --> 02:19:56,317
Where is he?

1434
02:19:56,541 --> 02:19:59,858
Where is Gondor's finest?
Where's my first-born?

1435
02:20:00,545 --> 02:20:02,204
Father!

1436
02:20:07,119 --> 02:20:09,421
They say you vanquished the enemy
almost single-handedly.

1437
02:20:09,656 --> 02:20:12,951
They exaggerate.
The victory belongs to Faramir also.

1438
02:20:14,561 --> 02:20:17,343
But for Faramir, this city
would still be standing.

1439
02:20:18,263 --> 02:20:20,467
Were you not entrusted to protect it?

1440
02:20:20,732 --> 02:20:22,674
I would have done,
but our numbers were too few.

1441
02:20:22,935 --> 02:20:24,562
Oh, too few.

1442
02:20:25,138 --> 02:20:27,439
You let the enemy walk in
and take it on a whim.

1443
02:20:29,742 --> 02:20:32,612
Always you cast a poor reflection on me.

1444
02:20:32,911 --> 02:20:35,082
That is not my intent.

1445
02:20:35,348 --> 02:20:38,959
You give him no credit,
and yet he tries to do your will.

1446
02:20:42,522 --> 02:20:45,304
- He loves you, Father.
- Do not trouble me with Faramir...

1447
02:20:45,558 --> 02:20:48,242
...I know his uses, and they are few.

1448
02:20:48,528 --> 02:20:51,976
We have more urgent things to speak of.

1449
02:20:53,300 --> 02:20:55,634
Elrond of Rivendell has called a meeting.

1450
02:20:55,903 --> 02:20:58,653
He will not say why,
but I have guessed its purpose.

1451
02:20:58,939 --> 02:21:02,583
It is rumored that the weapon
of the enemy has been found.

1452
02:21:04,945 --> 02:21:07,149
The One Ring.

1453
02:21:09,983 --> 02:21:14,456
- Isildur's Bane.
- It has fallen into the hands of the Elves.

1454
02:21:14,822 --> 02:21:18,303
Everyone will try to claim it:
Men, Dwarves, wizards.

1455
02:21:18,627 --> 02:21:22,588
We cannot let that happen.
This thing must come to Gondor.

1456
02:21:24,597 --> 02:21:27,151
- Gondor.
- It's dangerous, I know.

1457
02:21:27,435 --> 02:21:30,980
Ever the Ring will seek to corrupt
the hearts of lesser Men.

1458
02:21:31,305 --> 02:21:35,048
But you, you are strong.
And our need is great.

1459
02:21:35,377 --> 02:21:40,462
It is our blood which is being spilled,
our people who are dying.

1460
02:21:40,849 --> 02:21:45,705
Sauron is biding his time.
He's massing fresh armies.

1461
02:21:46,087 --> 02:21:47,516
He will return.

1462
02:21:47,756 --> 02:21:51,367
And when he does,
we will be powerless to stop him.

1463
02:21:51,660 --> 02:21:54,116
You must go.

1464
02:21:55,431 --> 02:21:57,438
Bring me back this mighty gift.

1465
02:21:58,367 --> 02:22:03,637
No. My place is here with my people.
Not in Rivendell.

1466
02:22:04,040 --> 02:22:07,586
- Would you deny your own father?
- If there is need to go to Rivendell...

1467
02:22:07,911 --> 02:22:10,757
...send me in his stead.
- You?

1468
02:22:12,049 --> 02:22:13,903
Oh, I see.

1469
02:22:14,151 --> 02:22:18,176
A chance for Faramir, captain of Gondor,
to show his quality.

1470
02:22:18,789 --> 02:22:20,697
I think not.

1471
02:22:20,957 --> 02:22:23,707
I trust this mission only to your brother.

1472
02:22:24,026 --> 02:22:26,809
The one who will not fail me.

1473
02:22:44,014 --> 02:22:47,047
Remember today, little brother.

1474
02:23:05,569 --> 02:23:07,456
Captain Faramir!

1475
02:23:08,839 --> 02:23:10,880
We found the third one.

1476
02:23:22,453 --> 02:23:24,363
You must come with me. Now.

1477
02:23:35,667 --> 02:23:36,681
Down there.

1478
02:23:51,683 --> 02:23:54,433
To enter the Forbidden Pool
bears the penalty of death.

1479
02:24:05,198 --> 02:24:06,606
They wait for my command.

1480
02:24:12,172 --> 02:24:13,219
Shall I shoot?

1481
02:24:14,507 --> 02:24:17,409
<i>The rock and pool
Is nice and cool</i>

1482
02:24:17,710 --> 02:24:19,465
<i>So juicy sweet</i>

1483
02:24:20,181 --> 02:24:23,028
<i>Our only wish
To catch a fish</i>

1484
02:24:23,316 --> 02:24:25,902
<i>So juicy sweet</i>

1485
02:24:32,959 --> 02:24:34,301
Wait.

1486
02:24:35,863 --> 02:24:38,580
This creature is bound to me.

1487
02:24:39,333 --> 02:24:41,188
And I to him.

1488
02:24:44,538 --> 02:24:45,783
He is our guide.

1489
02:24:50,578 --> 02:24:51,920
Please...

1490
02:24:52,146 --> 02:24:53,935
...let me go down to him.

1491
02:25:05,293 --> 02:25:06,885
Sméagol.

1492
02:25:07,963 --> 02:25:10,101
Master is here.

1493
02:25:11,433 --> 02:25:12,481
Come, Sméagol.

1494
02:25:15,437 --> 02:25:17,958
Trust master. Come.

1495
02:25:21,244 --> 02:25:24,920
We must go now?

1496
02:25:25,448 --> 02:25:28,743
Sméagol, you must trust master.

1497
02:25:29,050 --> 02:25:30,392
Follow me. Come on.

1498
02:25:31,654 --> 02:25:33,115
Come.

1499
02:25:35,691 --> 02:25:36,837
Come, Sméagol.

1500
02:25:37,393 --> 02:25:39,367
Nice Sméagol. That's it.

1501
02:25:39,962 --> 02:25:41,425
Come on.

1502
02:25:45,936 --> 02:25:47,496
Don't hurt him!

1503
02:25:47,770 --> 02:25:50,389
Sméagol, don't struggle.
Sméagol, listen to me.

1504
02:25:50,674 --> 02:25:51,917
Master!

1505
02:26:17,200 --> 02:26:19,437
That's enough.

1506
02:26:23,205 --> 02:26:25,278
Where are you leading them?

1507
02:26:27,177 --> 02:26:28,771
Answer me.

1508
02:26:29,646 --> 02:26:32,745
Sméagol.

1509
02:26:36,321 --> 02:26:40,893
Why does it cry, Sméagol?

1510
02:26:42,327 --> 02:26:44,848
Cruel Men hurts us.

1511
02:26:45,129 --> 02:26:47,999
Master tricksed us.

1512
02:26:48,334 --> 02:26:51,715
Of course he did.

1513
02:26:52,270 --> 02:26:55,783
I told you he was tricksy.

1514
02:26:56,140 --> 02:26:59,043
I told you he was false.

1515
02:26:59,344 --> 02:27:01,931
Master is our friend.

1516
02:27:02,215 --> 02:27:04,483
Our friend.

1517
02:27:04,750 --> 02:27:06,823
Master betrayed us.

1518
02:27:07,086 --> 02:27:09,955
No. Not its business.

1519
02:27:11,157 --> 02:27:13,491
Leave us alone!

1520
02:27:13,760 --> 02:27:16,062
Filthy little Hobbitses!

1521
02:27:16,329 --> 02:27:18,532
They stole it from us!

1522
02:27:18,797 --> 02:27:20,171
No. No.

1523
02:27:20,800 --> 02:27:22,360
What did they steal?

1524
02:27:24,603 --> 02:27:29,720
My precious!

1525
02:27:33,580 --> 02:27:35,140
We have to get out of here.

1526
02:27:35,815 --> 02:27:37,702
You go. Go, now.

1527
02:27:40,388 --> 02:27:42,176
You can do it.

1528
02:27:43,690 --> 02:27:45,097
Use the Ring, Mr. Frodo.

1529
02:27:45,325 --> 02:27:47,049
Just this once.

1530
02:27:47,294 --> 02:27:48,984
Put it on.

1531
02:27:49,497 --> 02:27:51,439
Disappear.

1532
02:27:52,565 --> 02:27:53,613
I can't.

1533
02:27:56,737 --> 02:27:58,876
You were right, Sam.

1534
02:28:00,442 --> 02:28:02,808
You tried to tell me but...

1535
02:28:07,648 --> 02:28:09,721
I'm sorry.

1536
02:28:14,356 --> 02:28:17,105
The Ring's taking me, Sam.

1537
02:28:18,627 --> 02:28:20,219
If I put it on...

1538
02:28:20,462 --> 02:28:22,699
...he'll find me.

1539
02:28:24,465 --> 02:28:26,353
He'll see.

1540
02:28:27,669 --> 02:28:29,556
Mr. Frodo...

1541
02:28:34,543 --> 02:28:38,635
So this is the answer
to all the riddles.

1542
02:28:41,016 --> 02:28:43,886
Here in the Wild I have you...

1543
02:28:44,186 --> 02:28:46,009
...two Halflings...

1544
02:28:46,255 --> 02:28:49,288
...and a host of men at my call.

1545
02:28:52,728 --> 02:28:56,077
The Ring of Power within my grasp.

1546
02:28:56,970 --> 02:29:09,259
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ I tuo i macil a staldaron Corma</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(The strength, the weapon, the needs of the valiant, the Ring...)</font></i>

1547
02:29:05,942 --> 02:29:09,486
A chance for Faramir,
captain of Gondor...

1548
02:29:11,280 --> 02:29:14,182
...to show his quality.

1549
02:29:35,406 --> 02:29:36,900
No!

1550
02:29:40,177 --> 02:29:41,454
Stop it!

1551
02:29:41,679 --> 02:29:42,660
Leave him alone.

1552
02:29:44,082 --> 02:29:46,448
Don't you understand?

1553
02:29:47,885 --> 02:29:49,707
He's got to destroy it!

1554
02:29:49,953 --> 02:29:53,053
That's where we're going, into Mordor.

1555
02:29:53,358 --> 02:29:54,951
To the Mountain of Fire!

1556
02:29:56,093 --> 02:29:59,061
Osgiliath is under attack.
They call for reinforcements.

1557
02:29:59,364 --> 02:30:02,234
Please. It's such a burden.

1558
02:30:04,536 --> 02:30:06,543
Will you not help him?

1559
02:30:07,972 --> 02:30:09,794
Captain?

1560
02:30:10,576 --> 02:30:12,681
Prepare to leave.

1561
02:30:17,750 --> 02:30:20,084
The Ring will go to Gondor.

1562
02:31:20,500 --> 02:31:25,450
<font color="#008000">Mae carnen, Brego, mellon nîn.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(Well done, Brego, my friend.)</font>

1563
02:31:33,127 --> 02:31:35,648
- He's alive!
- Where is he? Where is he?

1564
02:31:35,930 --> 02:31:38,865
Get out of the way!
I'm going to kill him!

1565
02:31:39,167 --> 02:31:42,779
You are the luckiest, the canniest...

1566
02:31:43,105 --> 02:31:46,967
...and the most reckless man
I ever knew.

1567
02:31:47,809 --> 02:31:49,238
Bless you, laddie.

1568
02:31:49,877 --> 02:31:51,536
Gimli, where is the king?

1569
02:32:00,689 --> 02:32:01,637
<font color="#008000">Le abdollen.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(You’re late.)</font>

1570
02:32:05,428 --> 02:32:06,704
You look terrible.

1571
02:32:33,800 --> 02:32:36,800
<font color="#008000">Hannon le.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(Thank you.)</font>

1572
02:32:48,472 --> 02:32:50,446
A great host, you say?

1573
02:32:50,708 --> 02:32:53,261
- All Isengard is emptied.
- How many?

1574
02:32:54,044 --> 02:32:56,914
Ten thousand strong at least.

1575
02:32:58,581 --> 02:32:59,988
Ten thousand?

1576
02:33:00,483 --> 02:33:02,850
It is an army bred for a single purpose:

1577
02:33:05,656 --> 02:33:07,696
To destroy the world of Men.

1578
02:33:10,294 --> 02:33:12,203
They will be here by nightfall.

1579
02:33:18,136 --> 02:33:19,380
Let them come!

1580
02:33:20,937 --> 02:33:23,589
I want every man and strong lad
able to bear arms...

1581
02:33:23,875 --> 02:33:26,875
...to be ready for battle by nightfall.

1582
02:33:35,220 --> 02:33:38,035
We will cover the causeway
and the gate from above.

1583
02:33:38,323 --> 02:33:40,658
No army has ever breached
the Deeping Wall...

1584
02:33:40,925 --> 02:33:43,542
...or set foot inside the Hornburg!

1585
02:33:43,828 --> 02:33:46,130
This is no rabble of mindless Orcs.

1586
02:33:46,831 --> 02:33:48,936
These are Uruk-hai.

1587
02:33:49,201 --> 02:33:52,496
Their armour is thick
and their shields broad.

1588
02:33:54,272 --> 02:33:57,785
I have fought many wars,
Master Dwarf.

1589
02:33:58,110 --> 02:34:01,558
I know how to defend my own keep.

1590
02:34:08,353 --> 02:34:11,616
They will break upon this fortress
like water on rock.

1591
02:34:11,925 --> 02:34:16,943
Saruman's hordes will pillage and burn.
We've seen it before.

1592
02:34:17,362 --> 02:34:19,917
Crops can be resown...

1593
02:34:20,200 --> 02:34:23,070
...homes rebuilt.

1594
02:34:23,803 --> 02:34:26,258
Within these walls...

1595
02:34:26,740 --> 02:34:28,169
...we will outlast them.

1596
02:34:28,408 --> 02:34:30,709
They do not come to destroy Rohan's
crops or villages.

1597
02:34:30,977 --> 02:34:32,471
They come to destroy its people...

1598
02:34:32,647 --> 02:34:35,035
...down to the last child.

1599
02:34:36,016 --> 02:34:38,188
What would you have me do?

1600
02:34:38,486 --> 02:34:40,111
Look at my men.

1601
02:34:40,388 --> 02:34:42,046
Their courage hangs by a thread.

1602
02:34:44,324 --> 02:34:48,547
If this is to be our end, then I would
have them make such an end...

1603
02:34:48,895 --> 02:34:51,798
...as to be worthy of remembrance.

1604
02:34:55,569 --> 02:34:57,392
Send out riders, my lord.

1605
02:34:57,771 --> 02:35:00,521
You must call for aid.

1606
02:35:03,911 --> 02:35:06,083
And who will come?

1607
02:35:06,581 --> 02:35:08,108
Elves?

1608
02:35:08,382 --> 02:35:10,324
Dwarves?

1609
02:35:11,219 --> 02:35:13,969
We are not so lucky in our friends
as you.

1610
02:35:14,922 --> 02:35:17,094
The old alliances are dead.

1611
02:35:17,626 --> 02:35:20,310
- Gondor will answer.
- Gondor?!

1612
02:35:20,596 --> 02:35:22,701
Where was Gondor
when the Westfold fell?!

1613
02:35:23,764 --> 02:35:26,863
Where was Gondor when
our enemies closed in around us?!

1614
02:35:27,170 --> 02:35:29,023
Where was Gon...?

1615
02:35:31,773 --> 02:35:33,561
No, my Lord Aragorn...

1616
02:35:35,245 --> 02:35:37,611
...we are alone.

1617
02:35:44,586 --> 02:35:46,277
Get the women and children
into the caves.

1618
02:35:46,523 --> 02:35:47,701
We need more time
to lay provisions...

1619
02:35:47,956 --> 02:35:51,305
There is no time. War is upon us.

1620
02:35:51,727 --> 02:35:53,354
Secure the gate.

1621
02:35:58,636 --> 02:36:00,642
We Ents have not troubled...

1622
02:36:00,937 --> 02:36:04,166
...about the wars of Men and wizards...

1623
02:36:05,074 --> 02:36:07,922
...for a very long time.

1624
02:36:09,312 --> 02:36:13,883
But now, something
is about to happen...

1625
02:36:14,250 --> 02:36:16,487
...that has not happened...

1626
02:36:16,787 --> 02:36:19,176
...for an age.

1627
02:36:20,490 --> 02:36:22,629
Entmoot.

1628
02:36:23,192 --> 02:36:24,120
What's that?

1629
02:36:24,595 --> 02:36:27,312
'Tis a gathering.

1630
02:36:28,632 --> 02:36:31,088
A gathering of what?

1631
02:36:36,970 --> 02:36:58,459
<i><font color="#008000">♫ Echuiannen</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(The woods have awoken)</font></i>

1632
02:36:49,120 --> 02:36:51,422
Beech. Oak.

1633
02:36:51,655 --> 02:36:53,510
Chestnut. Ash.

1634
02:36:53,858 --> 02:36:55,746
Good. Good. Good.

1635
02:36:55,994 --> 02:36:58,262
Many have come.

1636
02:37:05,904 --> 02:37:08,555
Now we must decide
if the Ents...

1637
02:37:08,841 --> 02:37:11,296
...will go to war.

1638
02:37:20,353 --> 02:37:23,287
Move back! Move to the caves!

1639
02:37:25,925 --> 02:37:27,867
Come on, people! Quicky, now!

1640
02:37:28,394 --> 02:37:30,565
We'll place the reserves along the wall.

1641
02:37:30,863 --> 02:37:33,003
They can support the archers
from above the gate.

1642
02:37:33,266 --> 02:37:36,264
Aragorn, you must rest.

1643
02:37:36,569 --> 02:37:38,871
You're no use to us half alive.

1644
02:37:39,438 --> 02:37:40,583
Aragorn!

1645
02:37:44,043 --> 02:37:46,946
I'm to be sent with the women
into the caves.

1646
02:37:47,247 --> 02:37:48,840
That is an honorable charge.

1647
02:37:49,082 --> 02:37:51,831
To mind the children, to find food
and bedding when the men return.

1648
02:37:52,119 --> 02:37:53,745
What renown is there in that?

1649
02:37:53,987 --> 02:37:57,533
My lady, a time may come for valor
without renown.

1650
02:37:57,991 --> 02:38:00,641
Who then will your people look to
in the last defense?

1651
02:38:00,961 --> 02:38:05,717
- Let me stand at your side.
- It is not in my power to command it.

1652
02:38:06,267 --> 02:38:08,950
You do not command
the others to stay!

1653
02:38:09,236 --> 02:38:12,848
They fight beside you because they
would not be parted from you.

1654
02:38:14,175 --> 02:38:16,281
Because they love you.

1655
02:38:23,484 --> 02:38:24,946
I'm sorry.

1656
02:39:30,920 --> 02:39:34,018
Farmers, farriers, stable boys.

1657
02:39:35,258 --> 02:39:36,950
These are no soldiers.

1658
02:39:39,330 --> 02:39:42,625
- Most have seen too many winters.
- Or too few.

1659
02:39:46,737 --> 02:39:49,518
Look at them. They're frightened.

1660
02:39:49,806 --> 02:39:51,214
I can see it in their eyes.

1661
02:39:56,014 --> 02:39:57,500
<font color="#008000">Boe a hyn:</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(And they should be...)</font>

1662
02:39:58,000 --> 02:40:01,150
<font color="#008000">Neled herain... dan caer menig.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(Three hundred... against ten thousand.)</font>

1663
02:40:03,022 --> 02:40:05,575
<font color="#008000">Si, beriathar hyn ammaeg na ned Edoras.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(Here they-will-defend themselves sharper than at Edoras.)</font>

1664
02:40:05,691 --> 02:40:09,212
<font color="#008000">Aragorn, nedin dagor hen ú-’erir ortheri.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(Aragorn, they cannot win this fight.)</font>

1665
02:40:10,262 --> 02:40:11,555
<font color="#008000">Natha daged dhaer</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(They are all going to die.)</font>

1666
02:40:12,263 --> 02:40:14,369
Then I shall die as one of them!

1667
02:40:20,905 --> 02:40:22,661
Let him go, lad.

1668
02:40:23,307 --> 02:40:25,196
Let him be.

1669
02:40:26,745 --> 02:40:31,981
Every villager able to wield a sword
has been sent to the armoury.

1670
02:40:36,421 --> 02:40:38,244
My lord?

1671
02:40:40,425 --> 02:40:42,847
Who am I, Gamling?

1672
02:40:46,364 --> 02:40:50,106
You are our king, sire.

1673
02:40:53,272 --> 02:40:56,402
And do you trust your king?

1674
02:40:58,077 --> 02:41:01,110
Your men, my lord...

1675
02:41:01,413 --> 02:41:04,098
...will follow you to whatever end.

1676
02:41:04,100 --> 02:41:26,700
<i><font color="#800080">♫ Hwær cwóm helm? Hwær cwóm byrne?</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Where is the helm? Where is the hauberk?)</font></i>

1677
02:41:11,092 --> 02:41:12,913
To whatever end.

1678
02:41:22,870 --> 02:41:26,285
Where is the horse and the rider?

1679
02:41:26,900 --> 02:42:00,700
<i><font color="#800080">♫ Hwær cwom feax flowende?</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Where is the bright hair flowing?)</font></i>

1680
02:41:26,907 --> 02:41:29,509
Where is the horn that was blowing?

1681
02:41:31,179 --> 02:41:35,370
<i>They have passed like rain
on the mountains.</i>

1682
02:41:36,551 --> 02:41:39,649
<i>Like wind in the meadow.</i>

1683
02:41:43,458 --> 02:41:47,070
<i>The days have gone down in the West...</i>

1684
02:41:47,929 --> 02:41:50,449
<i>...behind the hills...</i>

1685
02:41:52,499 --> 02:41:54,027
<i>...into Shadow.</i>

1686
02:42:02,577 --> 02:42:05,872
How did it come to this?

1687
02:42:27,337 --> 02:42:29,125
It's been going for hours.

1688
02:42:30,339 --> 02:42:32,609
They must have decided something
by now.

1689
02:42:32,876 --> 02:42:36,805
Decided? No.

1690
02:42:37,147 --> 02:42:42,068
We only just finished saying...

1691
02:42:43,486 --> 02:42:45,274
...good morning.

1692
02:42:46,690 --> 02:42:49,756
But it's nighttime already.

1693
02:42:50,060 --> 02:42:51,783
You can't take forever.

1694
02:42:52,862 --> 02:42:54,836
Don't be hasty.

1695
02:42:55,397 --> 02:42:57,667
We're running out of time!

1696
02:43:01,038 --> 02:43:03,884
Move! Move to the outer wall.

1697
02:43:21,326 --> 02:43:22,601
Give me your sword.

1698
02:43:32,169 --> 02:43:33,216
What is your name?

1699
02:43:33,838 --> 02:43:36,107
Haleth, son of Háma, my lord.

1700
02:43:38,343 --> 02:43:40,862
The men are saying
we will not live out the night.

1701
02:43:42,948 --> 02:43:44,835
They say that it is hopeless.

1702
02:44:02,734 --> 02:44:04,295
This is a good sword.

1703
02:44:06,438 --> 02:44:08,643
Haleth, son of Háma...

1704
02:44:13,113 --> 02:44:15,185
...there is always hope.

1705
02:44:38,205 --> 02:44:41,401
We have trusted you this far.
You have not led us astray.

1706
02:44:41,742 --> 02:44:43,203
Forgive me.

1707
02:44:43,476 --> 02:44:44,852
I was wrong to despair.

1708
02:44:48,115 --> 02:44:50,482
<font color="#008000">Ú-moe edaved, Legolas</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(There is nothing to forgive, Legolas.)</font>

1709
02:44:54,121 --> 02:44:56,804
We had time, I'd get this adjusted.

1710
02:45:00,361 --> 02:45:02,336
It's a little tight across the chest.

1711
02:45:08,602 --> 02:45:10,489
That is no Orc horn.

1712
02:45:16,277 --> 02:45:18,034
Send for the king.

1713
02:45:18,280 --> 02:45:21,726
- Open the gate!
- Open up the gate!

1714
02:45:21,970 --> 02:45:28,259
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ Man ammen toltha i dann hen môrn?</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Who brings to us this token of darkness?)</font></i>

1715
02:45:29,970 --> 02:45:38,259
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ Si danna atha nauva</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Now all will fall away)</font></i>

1716
02:45:39,970 --> 02:45:47,259
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ Mel, melmë nóren sina</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Love, our love for this land)</font></i>

1717
02:45:47,970 --> 02:45:53,259
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ Nur ala aëaron nur</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(is deeper than the depths of the sea)</font></i>

1718
02:45:53,570 --> 02:46:01,259
<i><font color="#0080C0">♫ Il[firin] nair[elma]</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Undying is our regret)</font></i>

1719
02:45:53,596 --> 02:45:55,109
How is this possible?

1720
02:45:56,186 --> 02:45:59,665
I bring word from Elrond of Rivendell.

1721
02:45:59,989 --> 02:46:03,088
An alliance once existed
between Elves and Men.

1722
02:46:03,926 --> 02:46:07,985
Long ago we fought and died together.

1723
02:46:10,433 --> 02:46:13,215
We come to honor that allegiance.

1724
02:46:13,500 --> 02:46:15,000
<font color="#008000">Mae govannen, Haldir.</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(Well-met, Haldir.)</font>

1725
02:46:21,845 --> 02:46:23,699
You are most welcome.

1726
02:46:29,153 --> 02:46:32,927
We are proud to fight
alongside Men once more.

1727
02:47:06,758 --> 02:47:09,889
You could have picked a better spot.

1728
02:47:14,900 --> 02:47:18,925
Well, lad, whatever luck you live by,
let's hope it lasts the night.

1729
02:47:25,276 --> 02:47:26,968
Your friends are with you, Aragorn.

1730
02:47:27,679 --> 02:47:30,068
Let's hope they last the night.

1731
02:48:30,144 --> 02:48:33,658
<font color="#008000">A Eruchîn, ú-dano i faelas a hyn...</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(O Children-of-Eru, don’t show the mercy to them...)</font>

1732
02:48:34,848 --> 02:48:37,052
<font color="#008000">an uben tanatha le faelas!</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(for nobody will-show you mercy!)</font>

1733
02:49:11,621 --> 02:49:14,303
- What's happening out there?
- Shall I describe it to you?

1734
02:49:15,690 --> 02:49:17,414
Or would you like me to find you a box?

1735
02:49:56,868 --> 02:49:58,112
<font color="#008000">Dartho!</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(Hold!)</font>

1736
02:50:20,691 --> 02:50:22,415
So it begins.

1737
02:50:28,400 --> 02:50:29,512
<font color="#008000">Tangado a chadad!</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(Prepare to fire!)</font>

1738
02:50:30,400 --> 02:50:31,512
<font color="#008000">Tangado a chadad!</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(Prepare to fire!)</font>

1739
02:50:37,510 --> 02:50:40,615
<font color="#008000">Faeg i-varv dîn na lanc...</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(Their armour is weak at the neck...)</font>

1740
02:50:40,879 --> 02:50:42,308
<font color="#008000">a nu ranc!</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(and beneath the arm!)</font>

1741
02:50:42,581 --> 02:50:44,207
<font color="#008000">Hado i philinn!</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(Release the arrows!)</font>

1742
02:50:49,321 --> 02:50:50,598
Did they hit anything?

1743
02:50:51,356 --> 02:50:53,265
Give them a volley.

1744
02:50:53,525 --> 02:50:55,500
- Fire!
- Fire!

1745
02:51:00,456 --> 02:51:03,456
<font color="#008000">I philinn! ... Han!</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(Arrows! ... forward!)</font>

1746
02:51:11,344 --> 02:51:12,969
Send them to me! Come on!

1747
02:51:32,599 --> 02:51:33,527
<font color="#008000">Pendraid!</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(Ladders!)</font>

1748
02:51:33,767 --> 02:51:34,814
Good!

1749
02:51:41,642 --> 02:51:44,512
Swords! Swords!

1750
02:52:22,752 --> 02:52:24,791
Legolas! Two already!

1751
02:52:25,087 --> 02:52:27,094
I'm on 17!

1752
02:52:27,390 --> 02:52:29,812
I'll have no pointy-ear outscoring me!

1753
02:52:36,698 --> 02:52:38,356
Nineteen!

1754
02:53:04,428 --> 02:53:05,802
Merry.

1755
02:53:10,267 --> 02:53:13,911
We have just agreed.

1756
02:53:24,081 --> 02:53:25,488
Yes?

1757
02:53:27,051 --> 02:53:31,044
I have told your names to the Entmoot...

1758
02:53:32,390 --> 02:53:35,422
...and we have agreed...

1759
02:53:36,026 --> 02:53:39,855
...you are not Orcs.

1760
02:53:41,799 --> 02:53:43,839
Well, that's good news.

1761
02:53:44,102 --> 02:53:48,063
And what about Saruman?
Have you come to a decision about him?

1762
02:53:48,873 --> 02:53:52,518
Now, don't be hasty, Master Meriadoc.

1763
02:53:52,844 --> 02:53:54,305
Hasty?

1764
02:53:55,147 --> 02:53:56,969
Our friends are out there.

1765
02:53:57,216 --> 02:54:01,210
They need our help. They cannot
fight this war on their own.

1766
02:54:01,720 --> 02:54:03,891
War? Yes.

1767
02:54:04,188 --> 02:54:05,978
It affects us all.

1768
02:54:06,258 --> 02:54:09,105
Tree, root and twig.

1769
02:54:10,129 --> 02:54:13,959
But you must understand, young Hobbit...

1770
02:54:14,366 --> 02:54:16,220
...it takes a long time...

1771
02:54:16,467 --> 02:54:21,169
...to say anything in Old Entish...

1772
02:54:21,540 --> 02:54:25,598
...and we never say anything...

1773
02:54:25,944 --> 02:54:29,687
...unless it is worth taking...

1774
02:54:30,016 --> 02:54:33,846
...a long time to say.

1775
02:54:34,787 --> 02:54:37,952
Seventeen! Eighteen!

1776
02:54:38,292 --> 02:54:39,273
Nineteen!

1777
02:54:39,927 --> 02:54:41,682
Twenty!

1778
02:54:41,961 --> 02:54:43,521
Twenty-one!

1779
02:54:53,707 --> 02:54:54,617
Causeway!

1780
02:54:54,700 --> 02:54:56,700
 <font color="#008000">Na fennas!</font>
<font color="#FFFF00"> (To the gateway!)</font>

1781
02:54:56,705 --> 02:54:57,987
<font color="#008000">Hado ribed! Hado!</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(Hurl to flow! Hurl!)</font>

1782
02:55:03,484 --> 02:55:05,752
Is this it?

1783
02:55:06,019 --> 02:55:08,835
Is this is all you can conjure, Saruman?

1784
02:55:35,317 --> 02:55:36,626
<font color="#008000">Dago han, Legolas!</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(Bring him down, Legolas!)</font>


1785
02:55:40,054 --> 02:55:41,167
<font color="#008000">Dago han!</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(Bring him down!)</font>

1786
02:55:41,423 --> 02:55:42,054
<font color="#008000">Dago han!</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(Bring him down!)</font>

1787
02:56:34,978 --> 02:56:36,287
Brace the gate!

1788
02:56:54,665 --> 02:56:56,837
Hold them! Stand firm!

1789
02:57:04,842 --> 02:57:06,119
Aragorn!

1790
02:57:10,815 --> 02:57:11,960
Gimli!

1791
02:57:17,700 --> 02:57:20,600
<font color="#008000">Hado i philinn!</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(Release the arrows!)</font>

1792
02:57:22,660 --> 02:57:23,608
<font color="#008000">Herio!</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(Charge!)</font>

1793
02:58:00,733 --> 02:58:04,530
The Ents cannot hold back this storm.

1794
02:58:05,472 --> 02:58:09,334
We must weather such things
as we have always done.

1795
02:58:10,309 --> 02:58:12,317
How can that be your decision?!

1796
02:58:13,079 --> 02:58:16,559
This is not our war.

1797
02:58:17,017 --> 02:58:19,122
But you're part of this world!

1798
02:58:23,356 --> 02:58:25,112
Aren't you?!

1799
02:58:29,262 --> 02:58:31,564
You must help. Please.

1800
02:58:32,866 --> 02:58:35,518
You must do something.

1801
02:58:35,937 --> 02:58:40,062
You are young and brave, Master Merry.

1802
02:58:41,441 --> 02:58:45,020
But your part in this tale is over.

1803
02:58:45,346 --> 02:58:47,484
Go back to your home.

1804
02:58:57,491 --> 02:58:59,663
Maybe Treebeard's right.

1805
02:58:59,927 --> 02:59:01,716
We don't belong here, Merry.

1806
02:59:01,963 --> 02:59:04,135
It's too big for us.

1807
02:59:04,433 --> 02:59:06,954
What can we do in the end?

1808
02:59:09,404 --> 02:59:11,891
We've got the Shire.

1809
02:59:12,573 --> 02:59:14,995
Maybe we should go home.

1810
02:59:16,945 --> 02:59:20,043
The fires of Isengard will spread...

1811
02:59:20,350 --> 02:59:25,052
...and the woods of Tuckborough
and Buckland will burn.

1812
02:59:25,421 --> 02:59:26,948
And...

1813
02:59:28,824 --> 02:59:31,759
And all that was once green and good
in this world will be gone.

1814
02:59:35,397 --> 02:59:38,213
There won't be a Shire, Pippin.

1815
02:59:57,854 --> 02:59:59,032
Aragorn!

1816
02:59:59,256 --> 03:00:01,525
Fall back to the Keep!

1817
03:00:01,792 --> 03:00:04,758
Get your men out of there!

1818
03:00:06,030 --> 03:00:07,459
<font color="#008000">Nan barad!</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(To the Tower!)</font>

1819
03:00:12,404 --> 03:00:13,897
<font color="#008000">Nan barad!</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(To the Tower!)</font>

1820
03:00:14,538 --> 03:00:16,131
<font color="#008000">Haldir!</font>

1821
03:00:17,007 --> 03:00:18,413
<font color="#008000">Nan barad!</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(To the Tower!)</font>

1822
03:00:20,344 --> 03:00:23,476
What are you doing?
What are you stopping for?

1823
03:00:24,007 --> 03:00:25,413
<font color="#008000">Nan barad!</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(To the Tower!)</font>

1824
03:00:32,767 --> 03:00:50,946
<i><font color="#008000">♫ Ar sindarn óriello caita mornië</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(And out of a grey country darkness lies)</font></i>

1825
03:00:42,767 --> 03:00:43,946
<font color="#008000">Haldir!</font>

1826
03:00:51,767 --> 03:01:11,946
<i><font color="#008000">♫ Ar ilye tier unduláve lumbule...</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(And all paths are drowned deep in shadow...)</font></i>

1827
03:01:26,747 --> 03:01:28,175
Brace the gate!

1828
03:01:30,483 --> 03:01:31,728
Hold them!

1829
03:01:33,553 --> 03:01:36,782
To the gate. Draw your swords!

1830
03:02:05,087 --> 03:02:06,941
Make way!

1831
03:02:09,924 --> 03:02:11,582
We cannot hold much longer!

1832
03:02:17,632 --> 03:02:21,048
- Hold them!
- How long do you need?

1833
03:02:21,402 --> 03:02:23,824
As long as you can give me.

1834
03:02:24,138 --> 03:02:25,698
Gimli!

1835
03:02:27,276 --> 03:02:28,552
Timbers!

1836
03:02:28,811 --> 03:02:30,698
Brace the gate!

1837
03:02:45,494 --> 03:02:47,120
Come on. We can take them.

1838
03:02:48,030 --> 03:02:49,591
It's a long way.

1839
03:02:54,903 --> 03:02:56,595
Toss me.

1840
03:02:57,840 --> 03:02:59,596
- What?
- I cannot jump the distance!

1841
03:02:59,876 --> 03:03:01,338
You'll have to toss me!

1842
03:03:07,050 --> 03:03:08,261
Don't tell the Elf.

1843
03:03:08,851 --> 03:03:10,543
Not a word.

1844
03:03:25,870 --> 03:03:27,244
Shore up the door!

1845
03:03:27,505 --> 03:03:29,481
- Make way!
- Follow me to the barricade.

1846
03:03:29,740 --> 03:03:30,754
Watch our backs!

1847
03:03:34,912 --> 03:03:37,050
- Throw another one over here!
- Higher!

1848
03:04:27,233 --> 03:04:28,575
Hold fast the gate!

1849
03:04:32,805 --> 03:04:35,619
Gimli! Aragorn!
Get out of there!

1850
03:04:40,513 --> 03:04:42,008
Aragorn!

1851
03:05:15,583 --> 03:05:17,917
Pull everybody back.

1852
03:05:18,385 --> 03:05:20,109
Pull them back.

1853
03:05:20,721 --> 03:05:22,128
Fall back!

1854
03:05:22,356 --> 03:05:24,723
Fall back!

1855
03:05:26,026 --> 03:05:27,652
They have broken through!

1856
03:05:27,894 --> 03:05:30,066
The castle is breached. Retreat!

1857
03:05:30,330 --> 03:05:32,469
- Fall back!
- Retreat!

1858
03:05:32,666 --> 03:05:35,154
Hurry! Inside. Get them inside!

1859
03:05:35,435 --> 03:05:37,608
Into the Keep!

1860
03:05:49,184 --> 03:05:53,919
I will leave you at the western borders
of the forest.

1861
03:05:54,222 --> 03:05:58,729
You can make your way north
to your homeland from there.

1862
03:06:04,667 --> 03:06:05,877
Wait! Stop!

1863
03:06:06,836 --> 03:06:08,264
Stop!

1864
03:06:11,441 --> 03:06:13,098
Turn around.

1865
03:06:14,077 --> 03:06:16,662
- Turn around. Take us south.
- South?

1866
03:06:16,945 --> 03:06:21,734
But that will lead you past Isengard.

1867
03:06:22,318 --> 03:06:24,872
Yes. Exactly.

1868
03:06:25,188 --> 03:06:28,286
If we go south, we can slip
past Saruman unnoticed.

1869
03:06:28,590 --> 03:06:31,143
The closer we are to danger,
the farther we are from harm.

1870
03:06:31,428 --> 03:06:33,337
It's the last thing he'll expect.

1871
03:06:36,032 --> 03:06:38,933
That doesn't make sense to me.

1872
03:06:39,236 --> 03:06:40,348
But then...

1873
03:06:40,571 --> 03:06:43,155
...you are very small.

1874
03:06:43,740 --> 03:06:45,431
Perhaps you're right.

1875
03:06:48,144 --> 03:06:49,607
South it is, then.

1876
03:06:51,214 --> 03:06:54,411
Hold on, little Shirelings.

1877
03:06:56,654 --> 03:06:59,337
I always like going south.

1878
03:06:59,623 --> 03:07:03,747
Somehow it feels like going downhill.

1879
03:07:04,528 --> 03:07:06,894
Are you mad? We'll be caught.

1880
03:07:07,164 --> 03:07:09,019
No, we won't.

1881
03:07:09,834 --> 03:07:12,005
Not this time.

1882
03:07:18,742 --> 03:07:19,724
Look!

1883
03:07:21,413 --> 03:07:23,748
Osgiliath burns!

1884
03:07:24,015 --> 03:07:25,421
Mordor has come.

1885
03:07:26,617 --> 03:07:28,887
The Ring will not save Gondor.

1886
03:07:30,355 --> 03:07:32,461
It has only the power to destroy.

1887
03:07:33,391 --> 03:07:34,765
Please...

1888
03:07:34,993 --> 03:07:36,553
...let me go.

1889
03:07:37,662 --> 03:07:39,189
Hurry.

1890
03:07:42,734 --> 03:07:44,076
Faramir!

1891
03:07:44,303 --> 03:07:46,692
You must let me go!

1892
03:07:47,240 --> 03:07:50,536
And those little family of field mice...

1893
03:07:50,844 --> 03:07:53,560
...that climb up sometimes,
and they tickle me awfully.

1894
03:07:54,412 --> 03:07:57,577
They're always trying to get somewhere
where they...

1895
03:08:08,928 --> 03:08:11,743
Many of these trees were my friends.

1896
03:08:12,565 --> 03:08:17,006
Creatures I had known
from nut and acorn.

1897
03:08:18,371 --> 03:08:19,517
I'm sorry, Treebeard.

1898
03:08:19,741 --> 03:08:22,391
They had voices of their own.

1899
03:08:24,745 --> 03:08:27,200
Saruman.

1900
03:08:27,680 --> 03:08:30,583
A wizard should know better!

1901
03:08:44,965 --> 03:08:48,445
There is no curse in Elvish...

1902
03:08:48,803 --> 03:08:51,355
...Entish or the tongues of Men...

1903
03:08:51,639 --> 03:08:53,876
...for this treachery.

1904
03:08:55,375 --> 03:08:58,093
Look! The trees! They're moving!

1905
03:09:02,918 --> 03:09:04,062
Where are they going?

1906
03:09:04,652 --> 03:09:07,751
They have business with the Orcs.

1907
03:09:08,389 --> 03:09:12,481
My business is with Isengard tonight...

1908
03:09:12,827 --> 03:09:15,347
...with rock and stone.

1909
03:09:21,726 --> 03:09:29,339
<i><font color="#008000">♫ Rithannen i geven</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Earth shakes)</font></i>

1910
03:09:29,726 --> 03:09:36,339
<i><font color="#008000">♫ Thangen i harn</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Stone breaks)</font></i>

1911
03:09:36,726 --> 03:09:45,339
<i><font color="#008000">♫ Na fennas i daur</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(The forest is at your door)</font></i>

1912
03:09:39,355 --> 03:09:40,404
Yes.

1913
03:09:41,590 --> 03:09:42,964
Come, my friends.

1914
03:09:45,626 --> 03:09:54,339
<i><font color="#008000">♫ Ôl dûr ristannen</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(The dark sleep is broken)</font></i>

1915
03:09:45,761 --> 03:09:48,386
The Ents are going to war.

1916
03:09:48,731 --> 03:09:50,423
It is likely...

1917
03:09:50,666 --> 03:09:53,800
...that we go to our doom.

1918
03:09:54,726 --> 03:09:59,339
<i><font color="#008000">♫ Eryn echuiannen</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(The woods have awoken)</font></i>

1919
03:09:55,604 --> 03:09:59,570
Last march... of the Ents

1920
03:09:59,726 --> 03:10:04,339
<i><font color="#008000">♫ I ngelaidh dagrar</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(The trees have gone to war)</font></i>

1921
03:10:04,726 --> 03:10:09,339
<i><font color="#008000">♫ Ristar thynd, cúa tawar</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Roots rend, wood bends)</font></i>

1922
03:10:09,726 --> 03:10:16,339
<i><font color="#008000">♫ Dam[bedir] ganed</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(The Ents have answered the call)</font></i>

1923
03:10:48,726 --> 03:10:52,339
Faramir! Orcs have taken the eastern
shore. Their numbers are too great.

1924
03:10:52,664 --> 03:10:54,605
By nightfall we will be overrun.

1925
03:10:57,502 --> 03:10:58,909
Mr. Frodo?

1926
03:10:59,271 --> 03:11:03,198
It's calling to him, Sam.
His Eye is almost on me.

1927
03:11:03,542 --> 03:11:05,931
Hold on, Mr. Frodo.
You'll be all right.

1928
03:11:20,393 --> 03:11:21,702
Take them to my father.

1929
03:11:23,361 --> 03:11:26,209
Tell him Faramir sends a mighty gift.

1930
03:11:28,769 --> 03:11:31,637
A weapon that will change our fortunes
in this war.

1931
03:11:32,905 --> 03:11:35,491
Do you want to know
what happened to Boromir?

1932
03:11:36,242 --> 03:11:38,893
You want to know
why your brother died?

1933
03:11:39,513 --> 03:11:43,091
He tried to take the Ring from Frodo
after swearing an oath to protect him!

1934
03:11:43,416 --> 03:11:45,238
He tried to kill him!

1935
03:11:45,485 --> 03:11:47,722
The Ring drove your brother mad!

1936
03:11:48,622 --> 03:11:50,377
Watch out!

1937
03:12:01,400 --> 03:12:02,482
Mr. Frodo?

1938
03:12:05,172 --> 03:12:06,928
They're here.

1939
03:12:10,110 --> 03:12:12,477
They've come.

1940
03:12:15,149 --> 03:12:16,971
Nazgûl!

1941
03:12:39,140 --> 03:12:41,213
Stay here. Keep out of sight.

1942
03:12:43,111 --> 03:12:45,251
Take cover!

1943
03:13:02,665 --> 03:13:04,159
The fortress is taken.

1944
03:13:05,035 --> 03:13:06,179
It is over.

1945
03:13:06,402 --> 03:13:10,177
You said this fortress would never fall
while your men defend it.

1946
03:13:10,506 --> 03:13:13,321
They still defend it.
They have died defending it.

1947
03:13:16,179 --> 03:13:17,520
They're breaking in!

1948
03:13:20,216 --> 03:13:22,606
They're past the door!

1949
03:13:26,055 --> 03:13:30,016
Is there no other way for the women
and children to get out of the caves?

1950
03:13:32,797 --> 03:13:34,651
Is there no other way?

1951
03:13:36,334 --> 03:13:39,268
There is one passage.
It leads into the mountains.

1952
03:13:40,070 --> 03:13:42,176
But they will not get far.
The Uruk-hai are too many.

1953
03:13:47,144 --> 03:13:49,445
Tell the women and children
to make for the mountain pass.

1954
03:13:49,714 --> 03:13:52,464
- And barricade the entrance!
- So much death.

1955
03:13:54,751 --> 03:13:58,013
What can Men do
against such reckless hate?

1956
03:14:02,870 --> 03:14:18,459
<i><font color="#008000">♫ Rithannen i geven, Thangen i harn</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Earth shakes, Stone breaks)</font></i>

1957
03:14:02,877 --> 03:14:04,201
Ride out with me.

1958
03:14:08,399 --> 03:14:09,926
Ride out and meet them.

1959
03:14:10,802 --> 03:14:12,841
For death and glory.

1960
03:14:13,138 --> 03:14:14,480
For Rohan.

1961
03:14:16,041 --> 03:14:17,448
For your people.

1962
03:14:18,242 --> 03:14:20,098
The sun is rising.

1963
03:14:21,970 --> 03:14:34,459
<i><font color="#008000">♫ Rithannen i geven, Thangen i harn</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Earth shakes, Stone breaks)</font></i>

1964
03:14:24,683 --> 03:14:27,552
<i>Look to my coming at first light
on the fifth day.</i>

1965
03:14:27,854 --> 03:14:29,195
At dawn...

1966
03:14:29,421 --> 03:14:31,047
...look to the east.

1967
03:14:34,970 --> 03:14:44,459
<i><font color="#008000">♫ Na fennas i daur</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(The forest is at your door)</font></i>

1968
03:14:35,260 --> 03:14:36,821
Yes.

1969
03:14:39,399 --> 03:14:40,959
Yes.

1970
03:14:42,401 --> 03:14:44,704
The horn of Helm Hammerhand...

1971
03:14:44,970 --> 03:14:52,459
<i><font color="#008000">♫ Ôl dûr ristannen</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(The dark sleep is broken)</font></i>

1972
03:14:44,971 --> 03:14:47,653
...shall sound in the Deep...

1973
03:14:48,208 --> 03:14:50,116
...one last time.

1974
03:14:50,376 --> 03:14:51,782
Yes!

1975
03:14:52,970 --> 03:14:58,459
<i><font color="#008000">♫ Echuiannen</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(The woods have awoken)</font></i>

1976
03:14:54,914 --> 03:14:58,558
Let this be the hour
when we draw swords together.

1977
03:14:59,970 --> 03:15:04,459
<i><font color="#008000">♫ i ngelaidh dagra</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(The trees have gone to war)</font></i>

1978
03:15:04,970 --> 03:15:11,459
<i><font color="#008000">♫ Ristar thynd, cúa tawar</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Roots rend, Wood bends)</font></i>

1979
03:15:06,492 --> 03:15:07,769
Fell deeds, awake.

1980
03:15:09,029 --> 03:15:10,075
Now for wrath...

1981
03:15:10,296 --> 03:15:13,559
...now for ruin and a red dawn.

1982
03:15:20,773 --> 03:15:22,945
<i><font color="#800080">Forð Eorlingas!</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Forth Eorlingas!)</font></i>

1983
03:16:05,733 --> 03:16:09,675
<i><font color="#FF8000">♫ [Ir]Kat-lu[hud]</font>
<font color="#FFFF00">(Shaft of light)</font></i>

1984
03:16:10,692 --> 03:16:11,870
Gandalf.

1985
03:16:19,234 --> 03:16:22,715
Théoden King stands alone.

1986
03:16:23,506 --> 03:16:25,545
Not alone.

1987
03:16:26,075 --> 03:16:27,155
Rohirrim!

1988
03:16:33,115 --> 03:16:34,228
Éomer.

1989
03:16:34,451 --> 03:16:36,871
To the king!

1990
03:16:38,100 --> 03:16:48,700
<i><font color="#800080">♫ For ðon hé wæs Sceadufæx</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(For he was Shadowfax)</font></i>

1991
03:16:49,100 --> 03:16:56,700
<i><font color="#800080">♫ hláford ealra méara</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Lord of all Horses)</font></i>

1992
03:16:57,100 --> 03:17:04,700
<i><font color="#800080">♫ Anhé Neandé hlá!</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(And he answered only to one!)</font></i>

1993
03:17:54,601 --> 03:17:56,290
Yes!

1994
03:18:05,543 --> 03:18:08,839
A hit. A fine hit.

1995
03:18:33,506 --> 03:18:35,874
Break the dam!

1996
03:18:36,143 --> 03:18:39,438
Release the river!

1997
03:19:01,049 --> 03:19:10,464
<i><font color="#008000">♫ Rithannen i geven, Thangen i harn</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Earth shakes, Stone breaks)</font></i>

1998
03:19:07,008 --> 03:19:09,626
Pippin! Hold on!

1999
03:19:10,649 --> 03:19:15,664
<i><font color="#008000">♫ Na fennas i daur</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(The forest is at your door)</font></i>

2000
03:19:15,900 --> 03:19:25,864
<i><font color="#008000">♫ Ôl dûr ristannen</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(The dark sleep is broken)</font></i>

2001
03:19:15,950 --> 03:19:17,764
Hold on, little Hobbits.

2002
03:19:26,049 --> 03:19:31,864
<i><font color="#008000">♫ Eryn echuiannen</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(The woods have awoken)</font></i>

2003
03:19:32,049 --> 03:19:39,864
<i><font color="#008000">♫ I ngelaidh dagrar</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(The trees have gone to war)</font></i>

2004
03:19:43,049 --> 03:19:53,864
<i><font color="#008000">Ristar thynd, Cúa tawar</font></i>
<i><font color="#FFFF00">(Roots rend, Wood bends)</font></i>

2005
03:19:59,295 --> 03:20:01,238
What are you doing?

2006
03:20:09,906 --> 03:20:11,400
Where are you going?

2007
03:21:09,634 --> 03:21:10,911
It's me.

2008
03:21:13,471 --> 03:21:15,576
It's your Sam.

2009
03:21:20,011 --> 03:21:22,565
Don't you know your Sam?

2010
03:21:40,332 --> 03:21:43,562
I can't do this, Sam.

2011
03:21:44,604 --> 03:21:46,514
I know.

2012
03:21:47,607 --> 03:21:49,875
It's all wrong.

2013
03:21:50,711 --> 03:21:52,652
By rights, we shouldn't even be here.

2014
03:22:00,186 --> 03:22:02,193
But we are.

2015
03:22:08,695 --> 03:22:11,598
It's like in the great stories, Mr. Frodo.

2016
03:22:11,898 --> 03:22:14,200
The ones that really mattered.

2017
03:22:15,336 --> 03:22:18,205
Full of darkness and danger they were.

2018
03:22:18,505 --> 03:22:21,353
And sometimes you didn't want
to know the end...

2019
03:22:21,675 --> 03:22:24,490
...because how could the end be happy?

2020
03:22:27,180 --> 03:22:29,254
How could the world go back
to the way it was...

2021
03:22:29,551 --> 03:22:32,811
...when so much bad had happened?

2022
03:22:33,822 --> 03:22:35,644
Victory!

2023
03:22:35,890 --> 03:22:37,383
We have victory!

2024
03:22:37,625 --> 03:22:41,399
But in the end,
it's only a passing thing...

2025
03:22:41,729 --> 03:22:43,007
...this shadow.

2026
03:22:43,231 --> 03:22:45,532
Even darkness must pass.

2027
03:22:45,800 --> 03:22:48,386
A new day will come.

2028
03:22:48,670 --> 03:22:52,467
And when the sun shines,
it will shine out the clearer.

2029
03:22:54,543 --> 03:22:56,813
Those were the stories
that stayed with you...

2030
03:22:57,079 --> 03:22:58,770
...that meant something.

2031
03:22:59,014 --> 03:23:01,470
Even if you were too small
to understand why.

2032
03:23:02,984 --> 03:23:06,694
But I think, Mr. Frodo, I do understand.

2033
03:23:07,023 --> 03:23:08,516
I know now.

2034
03:23:09,424 --> 03:23:11,530
Folk in those stories...

2035
03:23:11,794 --> 03:23:15,755
...had lots of chances of turning back,
only they didn't.

2036
03:23:16,099 --> 03:23:18,237
They kept going...

2037
03:23:19,001 --> 03:23:22,132
...because they were holding
on to something.

2038
03:23:23,872 --> 03:23:26,077
What are we holding on to, Sam?

2039
03:23:38,087 --> 03:23:41,862
That there's some good
in this world, Mr. Frodo.

2040
03:23:42,291 --> 03:23:44,812
And it's worth fighting for.

2041
03:24:11,854 --> 03:24:15,979
I think at last we understand one another,
Frodo Baggins.

2042
03:24:16,895 --> 03:24:20,669
You know the laws of our country,
the laws of your father.

2043
03:24:21,032 --> 03:24:23,137
If you let them go,
your life will be forfeit.

2044
03:24:27,605 --> 03:24:28,947
Then it is forfeit.

2045
03:24:31,743 --> 03:24:33,401
Release them.

2046
03:24:45,557 --> 03:24:47,532
Stay out of the forest!

2047
03:24:47,793 --> 03:24:49,516
Keep away from the trees!

2048
03:25:40,381 --> 03:25:42,104
Final count...

2049
03:25:42,349 --> 03:25:45,132
...42.
- Forty-two?

2050
03:25:46,720 --> 03:25:51,325
That's not bad for a pointy-eared
Elvish princeling.

2051
03:25:52,325 --> 03:25:55,839
I myself am sitting pretty on 43.

2052
03:26:00,102 --> 03:26:03,266
- Forty-three.
- He was already dead.

2053
03:26:04,171 --> 03:26:06,561
- He was twitching.
- He was twitching...

2054
03:26:06,842 --> 03:26:11,349
...because he's got my ax
embedded in his nervous system!

2055
03:26:13,749 --> 03:26:18,256
- He doesn't look too happy, does he?
- Not too happy at all, Merry.

2056
03:26:18,720 --> 03:26:22,104
Still, I suppose the view
would be quite nice from up there.

2057
03:26:22,458 --> 03:26:25,304
Oh, yes. It's a quality establishment.

2058
03:26:25,593 --> 03:26:28,311
I hear the staff are very good.

2059
03:26:34,103 --> 03:26:36,372
- What are you doing?
- Nothing.

2060
03:26:36,639 --> 03:26:40,731
- The world's back to normal, that's all.
- No, it isn't.

2061
03:26:41,077 --> 03:26:42,254
I'm starving.

2062
03:26:42,478 --> 03:26:45,445
Good luck trying to find something
decent around here.

2063
03:26:45,748 --> 03:26:48,682
Probably dead rats and moldy bread.

2064
03:27:12,709 --> 03:27:15,012
Saruman's storeroom!

2065
03:27:16,280 --> 03:27:17,228
South Farthing

2066
03:27:17,447 --> 03:27:20,066
I don't believe it.

2067
03:27:20,351 --> 03:27:22,325
It can't be.

2068
03:27:23,021 --> 03:27:25,802
- It is!
- Longbottom Leaf.

2069
03:27:27,258 --> 03:27:29,462
The finest pipe-weed in South Farthing.

2070
03:27:29,927 --> 03:27:32,797
It's perfect. One barrel each.

2071
03:27:33,131 --> 03:27:34,211
Wait.

2072
03:27:34,999 --> 03:27:36,177
Do you think we should share it
with Treebeard?

2073
03:27:36,401 --> 03:27:37,830
Share it?

2074
03:27:39,771 --> 03:27:42,073
No. No.

2075
03:27:43,675 --> 03:27:44,951
Dead plant and all that.

2076
03:27:45,443 --> 03:27:47,516
Don't think he'd understand.

2077
03:27:48,880 --> 03:27:50,986
Could be a distant relative.

2078
03:27:51,850 --> 03:27:54,272
I get it.

2079
03:27:54,552 --> 03:27:57,236
Don't be hasty.

2080
03:27:58,490 --> 03:28:00,148
Exactly.

2081
03:28:01,327 --> 03:28:03,498
Bar-hrum.

2082
03:28:29,222 --> 03:28:30,466
This is the old sewer.

2083
03:28:30,691 --> 03:28:33,625
Runs right under the river
through to the edge of the city.

2084
03:28:33,927 --> 03:28:35,585
You'll find cover in the woods there.

2085
03:28:36,762 --> 03:28:39,131
Captain Faramir...

2086
03:28:39,866 --> 03:28:41,622
...you have shown your quality, sir.

2087
03:28:44,205 --> 03:28:45,448
The very highest.

2088
03:28:46,007 --> 03:28:48,527
The Shire must truly be a great realm,
Master Gamgee...

2089
03:28:48,809 --> 03:28:51,623
...where gardeners are held in high honor.

2090
03:28:52,947 --> 03:28:54,834
What road will you take
once you reach the woods?

2091
03:28:55,615 --> 03:28:57,108
Gollum says there's a path...

2092
03:28:57,350 --> 03:29:01,124
...near Minas Morgul
that climbs up into the mountains.

2093
03:29:01,756 --> 03:29:03,414
Cirith Ungol?

2094
03:29:07,028 --> 03:29:09,483
- Is that its name?
- No.

2095
03:29:09,764 --> 03:29:11,357
No!

2096
03:29:12,300 --> 03:29:15,148
- Yes.
- Frodo...

2097
03:29:15,670 --> 03:29:19,052
...they say a dark terror dwells
in the passes above Minas Morgul.

2098
03:29:20,107 --> 03:29:22,529
- You cannot go that way.
- It is the only way.

2099
03:29:22,977 --> 03:29:28,989
Master says we must go to Mordor,
so we must try.

2100
03:29:30,752 --> 03:29:32,475
I must.

2101
03:29:36,058 --> 03:29:39,472
Go, Frodo.
Go with the goodwill of all Men.

2102
03:29:39,794 --> 03:29:41,736
Thank you.

2103
03:29:53,675 --> 03:29:57,635
May death find you quickly
if you bring them to harm.

2104
03:30:10,260 --> 03:30:11,754
Come on, keep up.

2105
03:30:15,298 --> 03:30:17,948
Mr. Frodo didn't mean for them Rangers
to hurt you.

2106
03:30:18,736 --> 03:30:20,492
You know that, don't you?

2107
03:30:21,371 --> 03:30:22,834
He was trying to save you, see?

2108
03:30:23,440 --> 03:30:24,869
Save me?

2109
03:30:25,308 --> 03:30:27,380
So there's no hard feelings.

2110
03:30:27,645 --> 03:30:32,501
- Forgive and forget.
- No, no, no hard feelings.

2111
03:30:32,883 --> 03:30:35,403
Gollum, Gollum.

2112
03:30:36,553 --> 03:30:38,244
Yes, master.

2113
03:30:39,390 --> 03:30:42,107
- Nice Hobbits.
- Very decent of you.

2114
03:30:42,393 --> 03:30:44,596
Very decent, indeed, Gollum.

2115
03:30:50,235 --> 03:30:55,220
Sauron's wrath will be terrible,
his retribution swift.

2116
03:31:02,579 --> 03:31:05,449
The battle for Helm's Deep is over.

2117
03:31:06,251 --> 03:31:09,634
The battle for Middle-earth
is about to begin.

2118
03:31:14,925 --> 03:31:18,220
All our hopes now lie
with two little Hobbits...

2119
03:31:19,364 --> 03:31:22,462
...somewhere in the wilderness.

2120
03:31:25,905 --> 03:31:29,165
I wonder if we'll ever be
put into songs or tales.

2121
03:31:29,474 --> 03:31:30,783
What?

2122
03:31:31,009 --> 03:31:34,752
I wonder if people will ever say,
"Let's hear about Frodo and the Ring."

2123
03:31:35,081 --> 03:31:38,211
And they'll say,
"Yes! That's one of my favorite stories."

2124
03:31:38,516 --> 03:31:41,332
"Frodo was really courageous,
wasn't he, Dad?"

2125
03:31:41,620 --> 03:31:43,212
"Yes, my boy.

2126
03:31:43,456 --> 03:31:47,100
The most famousest of Hobbits.
And that's saying a lot."

2127
03:31:47,426 --> 03:31:49,848
